title: irish creme
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Store in dark bottle in refrigerator at least overnight before drinking.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: peanut butter and jelly bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in beaten eggs; stir until mixture is smooth.
Reserve one half of mixture; press remaining half of mixture onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread grape jelly over crust in pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup Reese's peanut butter chips over jelly.
Crumble remaining dough over chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven immediately.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup chips.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: Cut potatoes into slices, about 4 cups.
Arrange slices, overlapping, in greased baking dish.
Combine pepper and paprika; sprinkle.
Sprinkle cheese over this layer and spoon soup over the cheese.

title: blueberry muffins(lo-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Lightly spoon flour into dry measuring cup; level with a knife. Toss blueberries with 2 teaspoons flour and set aside. Combine remaining flour, baking powder and next 3 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in the center of mixture. Combine yogurt and next 3 ingredients. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moist. Fold blueberries into batter. Spoon batter into 4 muffin cups coated with cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 18 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and cool on a wire rack.

title: frozen fruit pops
directions: Beat bananas until smooth.
Add strawberries, pineapple and juice.
Beat until well blended.
Gradually add milk.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into paper cups and put wooden sticks in middle or use popsicle makers.
Freeze for several hours.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and clear gel in a saucepan.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice, egg yolks and margarine.
Stir in the milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Cool.
Fold in sour cream and pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Chill well.
Top with whipped cream, pecans or walnuts.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop onion; place in pan with shortening.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add chili powder; mix well.
Place meat in casserole dish as first layer, then green lima beans and the corn.
Pour tomatoes over the corn; sprinkle with pepper.
Mix sugar and salt and sprinkle over each layer, except on cheese.
Top with grated cheese and parsley.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: all bran bread
directions: Put butter, brown sugar, molasses, salt and bran cereal into a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over all and stir until blended. Set aside.

title: cheese soup
directions: Makes 1 gallon.
Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in 6 cups water.
Saute onion in butter.
Make roux of flour and sauteed onion.
Slowly add chicken broth to roux.
Cook slowly, add milk, whipping cream, beer and boiled water with vegetables.
Next, add cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and cook about 1/2 hour or until onion is tender.
This sauce is good on pork or chicken.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale in a gallon container. Fill remaining gallon with water.
Freeze.
Thaw for approximately 5 hours at room temperature.
Add one quart ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together. Cut in the margarine. Peel, core and slice the apples and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle topping over apples, letting some topping fall between apples.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is brown.

title: tuna twist salad(reduced fat)
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine flour, sugar; add potatoes, eggs, corn syrup and evaporated milk. Beat well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350°F for 55-60 minutes. Serves 8.

title: catfish chowder
directions: Boil catfish until tender;
take
out all bones. To your broth, add cubed potatoes, onions, butter, tomatoes, pepper and salt.
Let all simmer for an
hour
or
more.
Then
serve with crackers.
The
amount of
these
ingredients
may
be
varied according to the number of people you want to serve.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla on low speed of mixer until light.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
If needed, add milk until spreading consistency.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange broccoli in flat baking dish and add cooked chicken.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into thick slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip in mixture and fry in oil.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in oil or butter. Add Tabasco to taste.
Put all ingredients in pot.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or as a soup with bread or crackers.
Serves 10.

title: chernobyl chili
directions: Sear meat in oil until brown.
Place in slow cooker.
Add tomato puree and beer to meat.
Add chili pepper, garlic, onion, oregano, paprika, salt and cumin to meat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Stir but leave the lid on as much as possible.
Add cayenne pepper and simmer 2 more hours, stirring often.
Add goat cheese and stir while cooking another 30 minutes.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions, green and red peppers.
Put in large bowl.
Add salt; mix well and cover with 1/2 gallon ice cubes. Let stand 3 hours.
Put in colander.
Rinse and drain well.
Put in a large pot and add sugar, vinegar, water and spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Put in jars while hot.
Seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: lynn's shrimp dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: fried squash or okra
directions: Mix corn meal, self-rising flour, cornstarch and seasoned salt in gallon size Ziploc bag.
Place sliced okra or squash in bowl. Beat water and egg together.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix. Drain. Put vegetables in bag and shake well.
Drop in hot vegetable oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven. Heat until bubbling hot.
Add sliced onions, cover and cook until onions are heated through (approximately 5 minutes).
Uncover and cook until onions are tender and dark brown.
Onions should be well browned before broth is added.
Combine onions, salt, pepper and broth; heat thoroughly (if canned bouillon is used, omit the salt and add 1/2 cup water).
Let stand on very low heat for 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Ladle soup into tureen and top each serving with one crouton round and 1/4 cup shredded Swiss cheese on each crouton.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or cheese is melted and golden brown.
Serve at once.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Drain berries; reserve juice, 1 cup, or add enough water for 1 cup.
Add soda to juice.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add juice. Add dry ingredients alternately with juice, sugar and egg mixture. Add berries.
Mix berries with mixer 1 minute or less.
This keeps berries from going to bottom of cake.
Use large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: vegetarian burritos
directions: Heat tortillas according to package directions.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Add carrot, onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce and next 7 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon about 1/2 cup vegetable mixture down centers of warm tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Fold sides over filling.
Serve immediately with salsa and guacamole.

title: crispy chicken roll-ups
directions: Top each chicken breast with 1 slice of ham and cheese.
Roll up; secure with toothpicks.
Dip in beaten eggs.
Coat with cereal flake crumbs.
Place chicken rolls in a greased baking dish; drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fish(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle salad dressing mix over fish fillets which are in a microwave dish.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Add small amount of water to keep fish moist.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Turn dish and cook another 2 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Sift and mix all dry ingredients.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients to the liquid mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can bake in 2 round cake pans.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk, egg yolks and shortening. Cook over medium heat until boiling. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans. Cool 15 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased 9 x 8 x 2-inch covered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: cauliflower supreme salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower and onion in large bowl.
Do not mix!
Cover with Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle bacon, sugar and cheese on top of Miracle Whip in order given.
Do not mix!
Cover bowl tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Toss well just before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sliced almonds on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until heated through.

title: red beans, rice and sausage
directions: Cut onion in small pieces and saute in oil in a large pot until tender.
Wash kidney beans and add to pot.
Fill with water about 2 fingers above beans.
Bring to hard boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium and cook for 3 hours adding water as necessary.
When beans are cooked wash sausage; cut into small pieces and add to beans.
Reduce to low heat and cook for 1 more hour.
When completely done, salt and pepper to taste.
Prepare rice and serve beans and sausage over rice.

title: best 7 minute white icing
directions: Combine sugar, unbeaten egg whites, water, cream of tartar and salt in upper part of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat constantly with electric mixer until icing stands in peaks, 7 minutes.
Remove and quickly add 1 cup marshmallows.
Beat several minutes and ice cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (pecans last).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Take a piece of dough in hand and roll.
Flatten with fork. Place on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Crumble 1 tube of crackers into mixture.
Place into casserole dish.
Crumble other tube of crackers onto ingredients; bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook, bone and cut chicken into chunks.
In a medium skillet, stir-fry chicken chunks in oil over medium heat.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, milk and syrup.
Boil while stirring to 230° or until mixture forms a ball when dropped into cold water. Remove from burner.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and peppers until onion and peppers are tender.
Drain.
Add eggplant, cracker crumbs, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, basil leaves and half of the cheese.
Pour into a baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or when cheese is a golden brown.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add vegetable oil and salt. Gradually add flour until dough is well blended and is not sticky to touch.
Let rise until double, 30 to 40 minutes.
Punch down. Spread to cover pizza pan.
Makes one large or 2 small pizzas.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream butter; mix with Baby Ruth and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Stir in other ingredients and chill.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers. Stir pudding mix into 3 cups milk; fold in cool whip. Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers; another layer of crackers; rest of pudding and another layer of crackers.

title: aubrey's barbecue sauce *
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer a few minutes.
Makes 5 cups.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine
cake mix, melted butter and one egg.
Pat this stiff mixture
into
a
13 x 9-inch pan.	Sprinkle pecans over this. Add powdered sugar to cream cheese and three eggs.	Mix and pour over
layer of pecans.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°, lower temperature
to 325° and bake 20 more minutes.
Cheesecake does not have to appear to be totally solid when removing from oven.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Have ready with baked crust a 10-inch quiche dish or a deep dish pie plate.

title: alanna's pork chops casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into a casserole dish or baking pan.
Put pork chops on top of potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and water together; pour over pork chops and potatoes.
Stir.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add Ragu sauce and parsley.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles while simmering (12 strips). Combine cottage cheese and set aside.
When noodles are done; drain.

title: creamy pesto pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain well.
Keep warm.

title: chicken spaghetti salad
directions: Mix spaghetti, Accent, lemon juice and oil.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight in airtight container.
Mix remainder of ingredients with chilled mixture.

title: u.s. senate bean soup
directions: Put soaked beans, ham bone and water in kettle and simmer until beans are tender.
Add mashed potatoes and stir until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer another hour.
Remove ham bone, cut up meat and return to soup.
Check seasonings. Serves 12.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pan. Store in pretty jars or to give away as hostess gifts.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add Ranch dressing mix, chili powder and garlic powder.
Add beans, hominy, Ro-Tel and stewed tomatoes (do not drain beans and hominy).
Simmer for 1 hour. Serve with cornbread.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of soup.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes, sausage and cabbage
directions: In microwave oven in a 3 quart casserole, mix well the potatoes, boiling water, butter, cabbage and onion.
Cover with waxed paper; cook on High 15 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in sauce mix, milk and sausage.
Cover; cook on High 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand at least 5 minutes or up to 1 hour.
Reheat on Medium if needed.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello, pineapple and juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Set aside to cool. Then add buttermilk and Cool Whip and mix. Pour in greased mold.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large glass or stainless steel bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve cold.

title: weight watcher's strawberry pie
directions: Mix water and cornstarch.
Stir over medium heat until bubbly (thicken just a little).
Sprinkle Jell-O and sugar in this mixture.
Dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Cool and add strawberries. Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.

title: pear pickles
directions: Wash, peel and cut pears into 1/4's.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar and water.
Add spice bag.
Bring to a boil and cook until pears are tender and can be pierced with toothpick.
Remove from heat and allow to plump in syrup overnight.
Pack in jar, leaving 1/2-inch at top.
Bring syrup to boil and pour over pears in jars. Remove air bubbles with knife.
Adjust lids. Process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: rolls
directions: Mix cooled milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs.
Mix yeast with 1 tablespoon sugar in the warm water.
Add flour.
Let rise.
Knead down.
Shape into rolls.
Put in greased tins.
Let rise.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until brown in 400° oven.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto a large cookie sheet.
Bake as directed.
Flatten dough with a spoon after baking to keep crust thin.
While crust is cooling, mix the cream cheese (softened), mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese, and dressing mix.
Spread evenly over the crust, then sprinkle diced vegetables on top.

title: cocoa peanuts clusters
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 6 minutes, counting from time bubbling begins.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Take from heat. Stir just enough to mix nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and add granulated sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and margarine. Beat until thoroughly mixed. Set aside. Mix brown sugar, margarine, flour and pecans until crumbly. Sprinkle on top of potato mixture. Bake in 350 degree oven until top is slightly brown.

title: steve's coffeecake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with shortening.
Add milk and egg; fold lightly and place in 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Spread batter generously with brown sugar and dot closely with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and cut strawberries.
Combine water, cornstarch and sugar.
Heat until boiling point and add jello.
Cool.
When cooled add strawberries, chill, then add Cool Whip.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix juice with all ingredients except fruit cocktail and nuts. Mix well, then blend in fruit.
Combine nuts with 1/2 cup of sugar and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Serve with whipped cream.

title: carrot squares
directions: Beat sugar and oil; add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes in ungreased 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan. Cool; frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make into 3 balls.
On floured surface, roll each ball out really thin.
Cut into 1-inch strips. Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook about 5 minutes on low heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 12 x 9 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 quart casserole dish. In large bowl, combine chicken, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Pour into bottom of pan.

title: musharoomaroom
directions: Butter hamburger buns and grill bottoms.
Spread bun tops with mayonnaise.
Combine mushrooms, artichoke hearts (drained), onion, salt and pepper.
Cook in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes. Spoon mixture onto bottom of buns.
Top with cheese and broil until bubbly.
Place 1 bacon slice on each sandwich.
Arrange lettuce and tomato slices on tops.
Serve hot, open-faced.

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and liquid ingredients.
Bake in large greased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pasties
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

In a large mixing bowl combine beef, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, soup, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper. Mix well: set aside. Prepare double pie crust recipe using mix. Divide dough into 6 equal portions. Roll out each portion on a floured surface to a 7 inch circle. Place heaping half-cup of meat mixture on each pastry circle. Moisten edges with water, fold in half. Seal edges and prick top with fork. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 25-30 minutes or until light golden brown. Eat from hand like sandwich or serve with mushroom sauce, or with a favorite gravy mix, prepared as directed.

title: crockpot potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in sauce pan and add sour cream and soup. Add dried onions. Combine with cooked potatoes in crockpot on low heat. Cook for one hour.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs.
Add mashed bananas and 2 1/2 cups flour with baking soda; add nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Make cheese sauce:
Blend butter and flour in saucepan.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add milk gradually.
Cook until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Set aside.

title: dirt
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk and fold into Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies (including cream filling) in food processor.
Cookies will look like dirt.
In large bowl, layer 1/3 cookie crumbs, 1/3 pudding mixture and continue layering, ending with the dirt (cookies).
Chill.

title: baked beef steaks for 2
directions: Rub steaks with lemon juice.
Sprinkle both sides liberally with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in shallow pan.
Lay sliced peppers and onion on top of steaks.
Add 1/2 cup water and cover with tinfoil.
Bake in a preheated 225° oven for 2 hours. Add more water, in small amounts, if necessary.
Yields 2 tender-as-butter, mouth watering steaks.

title: country corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put about 1 tablespoon oil in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or 10-inch iron skillet and place in oven until piping hot.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add liquids and slightly beaten egg.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into preheated pan and bake 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Let cream cheese get soft and mix in sugar, then peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust and put in refrigerator for about 3 hours.

title: spiced cranberry sauce
directions: Wash and pick over berries.
Combine all ingredients in a large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook just until cranberry skins begin to pop, 5 minutes or so.
Cool and refrigerate until served.
Keeps several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix with 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix 2 cups sugar, eggs, vanilla, oil and orange juice.
Add flour and baking powder.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Alternate batter and apples starting and ending with batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; add remaining ingredients, stirring to mix.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1 gallon freezer.
Freeze.
Let ripen at least 1 hour.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: german chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Unwrap and melt caramels with 1/3 c. evaporated milk at low heat in microwave; set aside.
Combine cake mix, remaining 1/3 c. evaporated milk and butter.
Combine by hand until dough is mixed. Press 1/2 of the batter in a well greased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle chocolate chips over the baked batter and spread caramel mixture.
Crumble remaining batter over top.
Bake for 15-18 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate applesauce bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs well, then applesauce.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cocoa.
Mix all together.
Pour in 3 buttered pans.
Fill about 3/4 full. Sprinkle top with chips.
Bake about 1 hour.
Insert knife in center; when it comes out clean, it's baked.
Let cool on wire rack.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice and then spread on a casserole dish.
Cook rice in a 200° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool this in refrigerator.
Boil pepper strips for 1 minute.
Rinse with cold water.
Add peppers, scallions and tomato to cooled rice.
Mix oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Toss with rice.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: One day before serving, drain beans and place in a glass bowl. Add green peppers and onions.
Mix oil and vinegar with sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over bean mixture; toss lightly. Refrigerate covered.
Makes 10 servings.

title: holiday yams and marshmallows
directions: Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layers of apple mixture and yams in a 1-1/2 quart ovenproof casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows; broil 6-8 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Serves 8.

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown meat in fat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
Blend thoroughly.
Cook over low heat 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and heat.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat egg whites
separate and add last.
Mix all ingredients together and
put
in
unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish sangria
directions: Buy a gallon of red burgundy wine and drink half of it.
Take a long nap.
When you wake up, if you want the mix to be a little sweeter, add more lemon soda to the mix and less wine.
Goes great with seafood and paella dishes!

title: cream of broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.

title: 2 coconut pies
directions: Combine all ingredients together and pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In casserole dish, combine noodles, tuna, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Top with Stove Top stuffing (dry) and Parmesan cheese.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: cheese ball or log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Blend onion and mayonnaise and add to cheeses.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Shape into ball or log.
Roll in nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Press crescent rolls into greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Put drained sausage on crescent rolls and 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Whip eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Cook rice and seasonings as directed on package.
Cool a little.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: country fruit bread
directions: Beat eggs; beat in oil and sugar.
Stir in cottage cheese and fruit.
Add to sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves or spoon into 4 (5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon pepper potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in round slices.
Sprinkle butter in bottom of baking dish.
Add a layer of potatoes on top of the butter.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of sesame seed and sprinkle on lemon pepper.
Add more butter.
Repeat layers with all ingredients until finished.
Cover loosely with foil and bake until tender in a 400° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken 'n biscuit triangles(makes 16 biscuits)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add mashed potatoes and chicken.
Mix egg with milk; add to flour mixture and stir until just blended.
Knead dough lightly; pat to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch squares, then into triangles.
Place on a greased baking sheet; bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 5 additional minutes.

title: "cheesy onion steak"
directions: Remove any bone from steak; cut meat in 2 pieces. Coat with mixture of flour and salt. Pound to 1/4-inch thickness. In 8-inch skillet, brown the meat slowly in hot oil. Top each piece with 2 onion slices; sprinkle with lemon pepper. Add 1/2 cup water. Reduce heat; cover and simmer. Heat 1 to 2 minutes to melt cheese. Makes 2 servings.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350 for 15 to 20 minutes.
Make three layers.

title: sugarless orange banana bread
directions: Mix all together, raisins and nuts last.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: honey cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and honey; add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; blend well.
Add nuts.
Chill dough.
Shape into two long rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill for several hours.

title: aunt vicky's lasagna
directions: Brown meat; mix spices, catsup, onion, garlic, tomato sauce and paste and simmer 1 hour.
Keep covered.
Mix all cheeses.
Boil noodles.
Add meat to sauce mixture after first 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, Bisquick and cheese.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, corn syrup, flour, salt, melted butter and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and cheese sub
directions: Place ample helping of ham, cheeses, lettuce, tomato, onion, pickles and peppers on bun.
Add Salad Supreme, salt, pepper, olive oil, vinegar and mustard to taste.

title: baked egg nests
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Separate eggs, keeping yolks in egg shells.
Beat whites, with a dash of salt & pepper, until soft peaks form.
Spread toast with ham; mound whites on top.
Make indentation with back of the spoon; slip in egg yolk.
Bake 20 minutes, until the yolks are set and egg whites are golden.
Serve with warm bacon.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of margarine (melted). Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat 2 sticks margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs on high speed for 12 minutes. Spread egg mixture over crust.
Layer sliced bananas, then well drained pineapple. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts and cherries. Chill 8 hours.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken pieces.
Place in a round baking dish or small roaster.
Put on some salt, pepper and garlic powder (to your liking).
Pour on Italian dressing mixture.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Larger chicken pieces will need an additional 30 to 45 minutes to bake.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds, paprika and chili sauce. Put into ovenproof dish.
Spread 1/4 cup chili sauce over top (enough to lightly cover).
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until piping hot.
Serve with cocktail bread.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add the lime juice and milk.
Beat egg whites and gradually add sugar.
Combine the two mixtures and pour into a graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip on top, if desired.

title: tony's egg sandwich
directions: In a small bowl, add small amount butter and then add egg. Beat and place in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
You may need to turn over halfway through cooking.
Place on bread and add cheese, if desired.

title: brownie pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Spread batter evenly into greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut into wedges.
Nice to wrap and pack in lunch box.

title: festive carrots and pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar, butter, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until clear and thickened.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Heat and serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cranberries and sugar; let stand for 30 minutes.
Add next five ingredients and mix well.
Gently fold in the whipping cream.
Chill before serving.

title: s'mores(tastes like some more)
directions: For each S'More, place piece of chocolate on a cracker.
Toast marshmallow and place on chocolate.
Top with second cracker. Squeeze gently and eat.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pecan pie bars
directions: Crust:
Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In large bowl with mixer at medium, beat flour, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press firmly and evenly into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Make a well, add remaining ingredients. Mix well until smooth. Put in 3 loaf pans (or 2 small or 2 big pans) that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350 degrees for about an hour or until done. Cool slightly, then turn out on to racks to finish cooling. Wrap in foil or plastic and store in refrigerator. Pecans can be added.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with layer of dried beef. Place 1 slice of bacon inside skinned and boned chicken breast. Spoon over top the mushroom soup and sour cream. Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: smoky beef spread
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and egg.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: easy banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffins cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg slightly; stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: applesauce raisin muffins
directions: Beat together egg, oil and applesauce.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into greased or paper-lined muffin tin.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Alternately mix in applesauce and eggs. Gently fold in mashed bananas.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Dust loaf lightly with sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef manawatu
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
To grease, add stew beef, onion and garlic.
Brown meat and add ketchup.
Cook until the ketchup turns brown (about 5 minutes).
Add consomme and parsley.
Cook about 10 minutes more.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Melt Crisco in a heavy skillet.
Add apple and onion; cook gently for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle curry powder and flour over mixture until blended.
Remove from heat and gradually add chicken broth and lemon juice.
Then add cream and mix well.
Return to fire and cook until thick.
Add salt and pepper.
Add shrimp, raisins and chutney; simmer for 15 minutes.
Do not overcook. Serves 4 to 5.

title: dee's carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, chocolate, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add pineapple syrup, eggs, oil and vanilla. Mix well at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add pineapple, carrots, pecans and coconut, if desired.
Pour batter into buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 90 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: "yummies"
directions: Line an 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil (dull side up).
Make 1 layer of crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: Put margarine in pot and saute onions and celery until clear. Add potatoes, water and all remaining ingredients, except the milk. Cook until potatoes are tender. Take half of mixture and blend until smooth; return to boil and add milk. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions 1 hour in salt and ice (1/4 bag). Rinse quickly and drain.
Pick out any chunks of ice left.
Heat vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric and ginger to boil.
Add onions and cucumbers quickly.
Return to boiling point; boil 3 minutes exactly.
Pack into 6 sterilized hot pint jars; seal with covers and cover with towel.
(They will vacuum pack themselves.)

title: rainy day butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine and egg together, add flour and sugar.
Mix in 3 additions.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet, crisscross with wet fork.
Add sprinkles and bake at 350° until edges are light gold.
Cool on cake rack.
Remove from pan and store in tightly covered container.

title: no bake cookies(heritage recipe)
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, and peanut butter, and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, powdered sugar and oats.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate boneless chicken for 24 hours in the fridge.
Grill chicken and baste with the marinade.

title: marinated relish onions
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Add dill weed.
Pour hot mixture over sliced onions in a refrigerator jar. Cover with lid; refrigerate until used.
Best to shake jar several times while cooling so marinade covers all onions.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream butter and brown or white sugar.
Add cinnamon, flour, pecans and bread or cake crumbs (moistened with cold water). Spread 1/2 of mix in baking pan.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onions and sweet pickles.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, mustard and salt to taste.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Add chopped eggs and mix.

title: royal icing(egg white recipe)
directions: Beat all ingredients at high speed for 7 to 10 minutes. Use immediately.
Reheating
will not restore texture so keep icing covered
with a damp cloth;
for making decorations and flowers that last.
It's a smooth hard drying icing.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all in 6 to 8-quart pot and stir constantly over heat until boiling point is reached.
Cover tightly and let set for a while before serving.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Scald enough glasses and lids for 1 1/2 quarts jam; drain.
In a 6 to 8-quart kettle, stir the blueberries, lemon juice and fruit pectin.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Stirring constantly, bring to a full boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove jam from heat.
Skim off foam.
Stir occasionally for 5 minutes, skimming off foam as it rises to the surface.
Fill glasses quickly, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Cover immediately with a 1/8-inch thick layer of melted paraffin.
Cool.
Cover.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Mix the English spread and butter together; add tuna.
Spread onto opened English muffins.
Bake on a cookie sheet open-faced for 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: dirt cake #2(a hit with kids and grown-ups.)
directions: Mix margarine with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Cream pudding in large bowl together with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Use 8-inch flowerpot.
Make sure you plug holes.
Layer crumbs and mixture into clean, new pot, beginning and ending with crumbs. Refrigerate overnight to set.
Garnish with several gummy worms and an artificial flower.
Can serve with clean new trowel.

title: georgia peach cobbler
directions: Combine fruit with sugar in a bowl; set aside.
Put butter in an 11 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place in a 350° oven to melt butter.
Butter should be bubbly, but not brown.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Drain and wash shrimp.
Mash shrimp until light and flaky with a fork.
Add shrimp to softened cream cheese.
Mix thoroughly. Form into ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill several hours or overnight.
Right before serving, top shrimp ball with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: lobster newburg
directions: In a small bowl, add sherry to beaten egg yolks.
Melt butter in medium saucepan and add cream; allow to boil gently for 30 seconds.
Add lobster meat and again let reach a gentle boil.
Add egg yolk mixture and season with salt and cayenne.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
A small amount of flour may be added if more thickening is needed.
Serve on buttered toast for 4 people.
If using pastry shells, size of pastry shells will determine how many people can be served.

title: baked spicy shrimp
directions: Melt margarine and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add all other ingredients, except shrimp and bread. You may want to use less red pepper and black pepper to be less spicy.
Adjust to your taste. Stir ingredients and add shrimp.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with the bread to dip into the butter sauce.

title: midge's pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, Crisco and salt until crumbly.
Mix water and flour to paste.
Add to mixture and roll out.
Makes 1 (2-crust 9-inch) pie.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onions in chicken fat, add rice and mix.
Put few drops of soy sauce in, add mushrooms and chicken soup.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: mom's monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Roll each piece of biscuit quarter in this sugar mixture.
Place layer of these in tube pan that has been buttered.
Sprinkle nuts over each layer.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Stir Miracle Whip and sugar together.
Layer cauliflower in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1/3 cup of Miracle Whip mixture over the top. Next layer in order:
peas, onions, 1/3 cup Miracle Whip, cabbage, remaining Miracle Whip.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Seal tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Stir if desired before serving.
Serves 12 people.

title: avys' hush puppies
directions: Put buttermilk in blender, add onion.
In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except the tomato juice or water.
Add the tomato juice or water until it is thick enough to spoon.
Drop spoon sized portion into 1 inch of preheated hot grease until golden brown, turning once.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly and thickened.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool.
Arrange peaches in crust.
Pour filling over peaches.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: deep dish chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients except for boiling water.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into a greased 9
13 pan and bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minute or until cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool and top with our favorite frosting.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and flour; mix well.
Pour out onto floured board; roll and cut out. Place in greased pan; grease top.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size (about 1 hour).
Bake in moderate hot oven at 350° until brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sugar, allspice, nutmeg and egg. Form into 24 meatballs; brown in butter.
Pour off excess drippings. Stir in soup, water and minced pickle. Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: angel hair pasta with broccoli
directions: Chop garlic and saute in small amount of olive oil until golden.
Add chicken bouillon, diluted in hot water or chicken broth.
Add one fresh tomato, skinned and cut up.
Simmer about 10 minutes, covered.
Add broccoli cuts, cover and simmer until broccoli is cooked.
Cook pasta according to directions on box; drain.
Pour broccoli/garlic mixture over pasta.
May use Parmesan cheese when served.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown beef cubes.
Transfer to Dutch oven.
Rinse skillet with cup of hot water and add to meat.
Chop bacon or salt pork and fry in skillet.
Add onions.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in paprika. Stir into beef.
Add uncooked green peppers and caraway seed. Cook slowly 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Stir in tomato paste and salt to taste.

title: old-fashioned strawberry ice cream
directions: Wash strawberries.
Remove and discard caps.
Puree berries in blender or food processor; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar, half and half, vanilla and whipping cream.
Stir in blended strawberries.
Pour into ice cream canister.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: "lazy daisy" oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy; gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats mixture.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch square or jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: double fudge saucepan brownies
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; immediately add 1 cup chocolate chips, stirring until melted. Stir in eggs and vanilla until blended.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending well.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chips and nuts, if desired.
Pour batter into a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325° or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen brownies.

title: liver and onions grandma's way
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Put onion into hot bacon grease.
Dip liver in flour (both sides); cook liver. Remove from pan.

title: patti's tasty taco dip
directions: Layer the dip in order listed in a casserole dish.
Keep refrigerated until served.
Then serve with favorite chips.
Plain tortilla chips taste yummy with this dip.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to package directions.
Cool and break into pieces in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; toss and chill for 2 hours or longer before serving.

title: hot wings
directions: Mix beer, wine, Italian dressing, hot sauce and some water together and cover chicken and sausage completely in lasagna pan. Let marinate for 2 or 3 days covered in the refrigerator.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until golden brown. Add meat and brown.
Sprinkle flour over meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce, water, vinegar, chili powder, salt and pepper. Simmer 20 minutes.
Line greased casserole with some sauce.
Add tortilla and top with grated cheese and sauce.
Repeat another layer.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and let set at least 1 hour or overnight. Serve in a hollowed-out round Hawaiian Bread bowl. Use the bread you removed from bowl for dipping.

title: no calorie brown gravy
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Add cornstarch; mix with water.
Pour into boiling contents and let thicken.

title: hot buttered rum(makes 4 cups - 16 servings)
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, brown sugar and butter. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until butter is melted and sugar is dissolved (6 to 8 minutes).

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage leaves in a container and cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Combine ground beef, salt, pepper, rice, poultry seasoning, onion and egg.
Mix well.	Cut center stem from cabbage leaf and place 1/12 of beef mixture into center of each leaf.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.	Heat oil in a large pot and brown each cabbage roll.
Mix tomato sauce, brown sugar, water and lemon juice and pour over cabbage rolls. Simmer on low heat for 1 hr.

title: spice tea
directions: Bring water to a rolling boil.
Add allspice, cloves, cinnamon and tea.
Stir well.
Turn off and steep 20 minutes.
Strain, or spices and tea can be put in tea ball.
Add lemon juice, orange juice and sugar.
Mix well.

title: zucchini sesame squares
directions: Saute onion, garlic and pepper until tender.
Add zucchini and saute a few minutes.

title: lazy daisy frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar; cream until smooth.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Spread over top of warm cake.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes, or until bubbly.
Cool cake slightly on wire rack before cutting.
There will be enough to frost a 9-inch square cake.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls (golf ball size).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain off any grease.
Add Barbecue Sauce and bake 30 more minutes.

title: beer batter shrimp
directions: Let opened beer stand for a few minutes or it will foam up when added to mixture. Shell and clean shrimp and split partially down back. Open and flatten slightly. Lightly mix flour and seasonings. Mix beer and egg together. Don't over mix. Dip shrimp in batter then flour mixture. Deep fry at 375 degrees until lightly browned. Drain and serve with favorite seafood sauce.

title: salsa roll-ups
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread evenly onto 10-inch tortilla shells (uncooked).
Roll shell into roll like a jelly roll.
Let chill and slice into bite size pieces.
Dip into salsa.

title: cheese strata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter deep 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Butter bread slices.
Make 5 sandwiches with cheese.
Cut into quarters.
Lay in baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with sage. Beat eggs with milk; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over sandwiches.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake 35 minutes or until set.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in the boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well after each addition.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter. Pour into 3 baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern frankfurter dinner
directions: Fry onion rings and green peppers in shortening.
Add frankfurters, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix as directed on package. Spoon carefully over frankfurter mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: crispy catfish fingers
directions: Slice fillets diagonally into 1-inch wide strips; set aside. Combine flour, salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine egg and milk; beat well and set aside.
Combine cracker crumbs and cornmeal, stirring well. Dredge catfish strips in flour mixture; dip in egg mixture and coat with crumb mixture.
Pour oil to a depth of 1 1/2 inches in a heavy skillet.
Fry catfish strips a few at a time in hot oil (375°) over medium-high heat 3 to 5 minutes or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in boiling water. Add the onion powder and lemon juice to this. Mix this with softened cream cheese and blend well.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all with Miracle Whip.

title: tamale bites
directions: Mix 1/2 cup enchilada sauce with bread crumbs.
Add salt.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on shallow cookie sheet.
Makes about 60 balls.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: favorite chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, celery, dates, sour cream, juices, onions, pimiento, salt and pepper sauce to taste.
Garnish with oranges and almonds.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and cover bottom of pan; cover with pork chops, salt and pepper.
Heat 1 can cream of mushroom soup and pour over pork chops.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mincemeat upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch square pan.
Spread mincemeat and nuts over butter.

title: caramels
directions: Bring all ingredients except 1 of the cartons of whipping cream to a boil and gradually stir in the remaining 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Cook to hard ball (250°) stage and pour into greased pan. Let cool; cut into squares and wrap in waxed paper.

title: hobo hamburgers
directions: Prepare hamburger patties and season with salt.
Place patty in double thickness, heavy-duty aluminum foil, large enough to enclose patty.
Place vegetable slices on patties and sprinkle with onion soup mix; add a pat of butter.

title: date balls - energy saver
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and microwave to slow boiling point. Stir in pecans and Rice Krispies.
When cool, form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Energy saver.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Use a 9-inch pre-made crust.
Cream together cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and sour cream.
Place on bottom of pie crust.

title: garlic cheese rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Remove when browned.
Brush tops with garlic butter.

title: orange butter
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add orange juice and powdered sugar; beat until thoroughly blended.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: turkey chip salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Chill until serving time.
Stir in coconut chips.
Pile on salad greens and garnish with additional chips.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marshmallow cherry bars
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and flour and press in ungreased pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes; cool.
Soften gelatin in water.
Combine white sugar and juice drained from cherries and water to make 1/2 cup.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in softened gelatin.
Beat at medium speed until very stiff, about 20 minutes.
(Mixture climbs beaters as it thickens.)
Fold in cherries, nuts, food coloring and almond extract.
Spread on top of baked crust.
Let stand at room temperature until it sets.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Peel hard-cooked eggs.
Combine sausage, parsley, sage, salt and pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Divide sausage mixture.
Press meat mixture around egg with hand, keeping the oval sausage shape.
Sprinkle eggs with flour, coating lightly on all sides.
Dip into beaten egg and roll in crumbs.
Heat oil in deep fryer or deep heavy pan to 350° on deep fat thermometer. Cook one egg at a time for about 4 to 5 minutes until brown. Drain, cool and refrigerate.
Serve hot or slice in half and serve cold.

title: won ton
directions: Stir all ingredients together, spoon mixture into won ton squares and wrap.
Deep fry for 5 sec. each.

title: corkscrew chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Mix Italian dressing with macaroni while hot. Cool and add cooked chicken breast. Mix remaining ingredients and add to mixture and chill. Serves 6.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; drain shrimp and crab meat.
Combine ingredients and add enough Miracle Whip to have mixture hold together.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator and enjoy when cooled.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Whip the 4 packages of Dream Whip.
Mix together cream cheese, milk, sugar and Dream Whip.
Melt one stick of margarine; add 3 cups of graham cracker crumbs.
Put 1/2 crumb mix in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, then 1/2 whipped ingredients on top of crumbs. Top with pie filling.
Cover with remaining whipped ingredients. Put the rest of graham cracker mix on top of all.
Put in refrigerator to set overnight (can use any favorite pie filling flavor).

title: tricky chicken(named by jennifer harris, granddaughter)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and cheese.
Beat egg (or egg whites) and milk together.
Dip in egg mixture and then coat with crumb mixture.
Place on nonstick or foil lined shallow pan. Bake about 50 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Do not cover and do not turn.

title: sundae sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in small saucepan; blend in water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Reduce heat to low and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in pickling salt and water for 5 to 7 days. Drain and wash cucumbers.
Cover with water and add alum.
Boil 10 minutes. Drain and wash.
Cover with water and add ginger.
Boil 10 minutes. Drain and wash. Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Place celery seed, allspice, cloves and cinnamon in a small bag and add to cucumbers. Boil for 30 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 pints of pickles. Very good!

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, pineapple, mango pepper, salt and onion.
Add 1 cup pecans and mix well. Shape in balls or logs and roll in the remainder of pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water together.
Add oil, salt and flour. Let stand 8 hours or overnight in the refrigerator. Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out as if making pie crust.
Cut into 8 sections the shape of pie pieces.
Roll wide edge first.
Then to point and place on greased cookie sheet. Let rise 6 hours. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
The time lapse necessary in this recipe make it perfect for Sunday dinner after church.

title: onion-noodleburger skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Makes 5 servings.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions into rings.
Saute in margarine until transparent.
Layer one half onions in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese, then with crushed crackers.
Repeat the layer of onions and cheese.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 30 minutes until browned.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef; crumble and drain excess fat.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, sugar, thyme, oregano and garlic.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter or oleo.
Add to sauce.
(If sauce seems to be too thick, add more tomato sauce or ketchup.) Simmer for at least 1 hour or cook in crock-pot on low heat for most of day.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch pan with chicken.
Put chicken soup over top. Mix dressing with eggs, onion and milk; put on top of soup.
Pour broth (or 1/2 cup water) over all and 2 tablespoons margarine. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: self-rising fruit or berry pie
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Remove from oven; cool slightly.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, flour and milk in this order. Stir to a smooth batter.
Pour into baking dish over melted oleo. Do not stir.
Combine fruit and lemon juice.
Pour into center of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beet cake
directions: Cake will have crack on top and crust will be crisp.

title: mexican salad
directions: Make salad.
Grated cheese on top of salad and break up Doritos.
Brown beef and onion; blend in beans and pour over salad while hot.
Serves 4.

title: light scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
In a sauce pan, heat water, bouillon and garlic until bouillon is dissolved; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 1-1/4 to 1-1/2 hours or until tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.

title: jello lime mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, then add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually add cream cheese to Jell-O mixture.
Mix well. Chill until almost firm; fold in marshmallows, nuts and pineapples.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: eric's ranger stew
directions: Brown ground beef and season with salt, pepper and Lawry's seasoned salt.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain fat.
Place crescent rolls on 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides of pan to form crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with hash browns.
Top with cheese.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, egg and molasses then dry ingredients and spices.
Spoon batter in size of walnuts and dip tops in sugar.
Press on buttered cookie sheet until rather thin. Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Can freeze.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Uncover and cook until desired consistency.
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken with broccoli
directions: Place chicken in a 9-inch square pan, and drizzle with butter. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix together crushed vanilla wafers, 3/4 can chocolate syrup. Butter sides of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Press cookie mixture in pan with hands (wet hands).
Pour softened ice cream over cookie mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Freeze overnight.
Decorate top with left over chocolate syrup and nuts.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla; pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well. Shape into balls or crescents.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Do not brown. Roll warm cookies in additional powdered sugar.
Makes 54 to 60 cookies.

title: carrot salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first seven ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Add vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: french peas
directions: In a saucepan, cook onions and lettuce in oil for 5 minutes. Set aside.
Combine flour with water and add to onion mixture. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add peas, water chestnuts and pepper.
Heat through and serve.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey and onions.
Drain and add beans, tomatoes, soul food seasoning and chili powder to taste.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: reuben baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 425° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
In bowl, combine the corned beef, sauerkraut and caraway seed.
Cut potatoes, leaving shells intact.
Mash potatoes with cream cheese. Stir into corned beef mixture.
Mound potato mixture into shells. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Return to oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes and blot well with paper towel.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch Pam-sprayed baking dish; cover with about 1 1/2 cups of bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add egg, oil and milk.
Mix.
Batter will be lumpy.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Add milk to fill line.
Proceed in the process of making ice cream in your ice cream churn.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets.
Place in container and add sliced carrots.
Pour Italian salad dressing over all vegetables, mixing to coat evenly.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: onion-olive focaccia
directions: Cook onion in 1 tablespoon of oil until tender.
Combine mustard and red pepper and set aside.
Brush bread with other tablespoon of oil.
Spread mustard over, then sprinkle with onions, olives and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 7 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: drop cookies with dates
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop on baking sheet with teaspoon. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry molded salad
directions: Stir all with wire whisk.
Add drop of lemon juice.
Put cut apples, nuts and a banana, if you want.
Pour into a mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Mash and whip potatoes.
Mix all ingredients and pour in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover top with marshmallows just before removing from oven.
Brown and serve.

title: gullixson crab
directions: Process first 5 ingredients in a food processor until smooth. Shape cheese mixture into 1-inch thick circle on a platter. Combine chili sauce and horseradish; pour over cheese round.
Top with crabmeat; garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 10 servings.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugars, vanilla and pudding; beat until smooth. Beat in eggs.
Gradually stir in dry ingredients, chips and nuts. Batter will be stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and cook; crumble and set aside.
Beat eggs, milk and remaining ingredients.
Pour all into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
If desired, add 1 soup can of water for more gravy.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours. It makes its own gravy.

title: caramel apple walnut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, baking soda and salt; cut in margarine until crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups mixture; press remainder onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Dice tomato into very small pieces (almost liquidly) and put tomatoes and juice in large bowl.
Chop small bunch cilantro into small enough pieces to where you could eat it.
Add in bowl.
Chop green onion and add in bowl.
Add jalapenos (to your taste; maybe about 2 or 3), a couple carrots and onion in mixer and mix until creamy.
Add to salsa.

title: toasted coconut butter balls
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.

Add vanilla and cream until fluffy. Add flour all at once and blend. Add coconut and mix well. Shape into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Chill 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until delicately brown. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: tomatosalata(tomato and feta cheese salad)
directions: Remove stem ends of tomatoes.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes. (Makes about 5 cups).
Place in medium sized bowl.
Beat garlic, oregano, salt and pepper into lemon juice.
Blend in olive oil and beat well.
Set aside for 10 minutes to allow flavors to blend. Toss cheese and olives with cubed tomatoes.
Pour dressing over and toss gently.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with fried cheese sandwiches.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar and press into 10
x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, lemon juice, flour and baking powder.
Mix and pour on top of pastry.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Upon removing from oven, sprinkle with additional powdered sugar; cool and cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Layer potatoes in bottom of Pyrex dish. Add layer of onion and a layer of bacon.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and let cool.
Add eggs and beat well, then add flour, nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake in 13 x 11-inch greased and floured pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: moon cake
directions: Put butter or margarine in a 3-quart saucepan and add hot water.
Heat to boiling and stir until butter is melted.
Add flour all at once to boiling mixture, stirring constantly until mixture leaves side of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each egg, until very smooth.
Spread on greased cookie sheet pan and bake until brown, about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt chocolate mixture in the top of a double boiler.
When smooth, dip and place on wax paper to dry.

title: macaroon tart shells(from "light and easy cooking")
directions: Combine ingredients; stir well.
Divide into 12 for muffin cups or smaller for mini-tarts.
Can fill with coconut cream pudding when cooled. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: dessert waffles
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients.
Lightly
beat whole eggs.
Add cream. Stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Serve with ice cream or sweetened fresh fruit.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, toss rice, chicken, celery and 3/4 of cheese and the salsa.
In small bowl, mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add to rice/chicken mixture.
Put in large baking dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese and chips.
Bake until bubbly.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In 2-quart shallow casserole dish, arrange broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, milk and pepper; pour over chicken. Combine crushed crackers, cheese and paprika; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate candies
directions: Beat cream cheese with vanilla.
Sift sugar and cocoa together; mix with cream cheese.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Press a pecan half on each piece.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in a large boiler with ample water until tender.
Set aside to cool.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup, poppy seed and broth together until smooth.
Tear chicken from bone into bite size pieces and add to mixture.

title: easy waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple well also drain cocktail.
Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir in cool whip and serve.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Blend well the milk, vanilla and 2 envelopes of whipped topping mix.
Whip at high speed until the topping peaks, about 2 minutes.
Whip 2 minutes longer.
Add sugar and cream cheese. Beat until smooth.

title: green salad dressing - french
directions: Put
all ingredients into blender.
Blend for 1 minute. Store in a jar in the refrigerator.

title: onion sauce
directions: Boil onions until tender; mince fine.
Boil milk; add butter, salt and pepper.
Stir in minced onion and flour which has been moistened with milk.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix altogether with hands.
Roll into quarter-size balls and roll in sugar.
Store in jar or Tupperware.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine the flour, brown sugar, butter or margarine and salt and rub the mixture between the hands to form crumbs.
Dissolve the baking soda in the water and combine with the molasses.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Place in 1-quart baking dish. Cool and freeze. To serve, thaw slightly and top with the bacon. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Very good.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Pour into crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn oven down to 350° and bake for about 25 minutes more.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Blend flour, sugar and milk.
Add fruit.
Pour mixture into pan with butter.
Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix sausage with Bisquick.
Mix well with hands.
Melt cheese and add to mixture.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: baked catfish
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Whisk together egg white and milk.
Drip fillets in milk mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place on a foil-lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle fillets with sesame seed and coat each fillet with cooking spray.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine the ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to a good boil and then let cool.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Spread over whatever.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix as you do bread.
Let rise.
Mix down and rise again. Place in loaf pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Serve warm.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onion and ground beef; drain off all fat very well.
Add remaining ingredients; heat well.
Serve with grated cheese or sour cream, etc.

title: sour cream breakfast cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and fluffy.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat again.
Blend in the cake mix, sour cream and nuts.
Pour half the batter into a well-greased Bundt pan.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt oleo and pour over 26 pretzels.
Add sugar and mix together.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add carrots, eggs and pineapple. Sift rest of dry ingredients and add all ingredients together. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: dilly oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters and remove any shell bits.
Reserve liquid. Scald milk and cream.
Cook oysters in the reserved liquid until the edges start to curl.
Stir mixture into the milk and cream. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into heated plates and add a pat of butter and a generous sprinkle of fresh dill.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in thin slices.
Put in deep casserole dish.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Add to potatoes, along with water.
Cut butter in small pieces and layer over ingredients.
Cover with favorite pastry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow cups
directions: You will need 30 paper cupcake liners.

title: kourambiethes
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add egg yolk, flavorings and almonds, beating until well blended.
Remove from beater and gradually add sifted flour to make a soft dough. Pinch off pieces of dough and shape into various designs, crescent, round or oval.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 1-inch apart.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes, or until very lightly browned.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Carefully place on flat surface which has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over cookies.
Cool.
Make 5 dozen.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Drain grapefruit well, but keep juice!
Heat 1/2 cup of juice (microwave is fine) and add marshmallows.
Cook on low heat until the marshmallows are melted.
Watch carefully and stir as needed. Fold in grapefruit sections, pour into the crust.
Refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.
May be frozen.
Top with whipped cream when served.
Is great after a heavy dinner.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Stir well and set aside. Combine
butter and sugar and cream well.
Add egg;
mix well. Mix bananas
and buttermilk and add to creamed mixture alternately with
dry
ingredients,
stirring only until combined. Pour
into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.

title: date cake
directions: Pour hot water and soda over dates and let cool.
Mix together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Mix all ingredients together and add vanilla. Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: pork roast with sauerkraut
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork in a 3-quart glass casserole.
Bury pork fat side down in the middle of the mixture. Cover.
Microwave at Power level 5 for 15 minutes.
Turn pork fat side up.
Insert temperature probe.
Microwave, uncovered, at Power level 5 until internal temperature of meat reaches 170°. Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before serving to complete cooking.

title: hash browns
directions: Boil 3 medium potatoes; chill.
Peel and shred to make 3 cups.
Add 1 to 2 Tbsp grated onion, 1 Tsp salt and dash pepper. Melt 1/4 c butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Put potatoes into a pan, leaving 1/2 inch space around edge.
Brown about 9 minutes. Reduce heat
if necessary.
Cut with spatula to make 4 wedges; turn.
Brown 7 minutes longer, till golden.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix milk with eggs.
Sift 1 1/2 cups of flour with salt and baking powder.
Pour milk and egg mixture into flour and blend well.
Add only as much more flour as needed to make the batter not too thick to flow.

title: unstuffed cabbage soup
directions: Combine soup ingredients in large heavy pot and bring to a boil over medium high heat while preparing meatballs.

title: olive surprises
directions: Cream butter or margarine and Cheddar cheese until blended. Add remaining ingredients, except olives, and mix well.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes.
Shape a small portion of dough around each olive. Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
If desired, these may be frozen on cookie sheet, put in plastic bags and stored in freezer until needed.
Best served hot.

title: zucchini mushroom quiche
directions: Layer zucchini, cheese, mushrooms and bacon crumbs on bottom of pie shell.
Beat together eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top with parsley flakes. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Place cut up rhubarb in saucepan and add water to cover half the rhubarb.
Stir in tapioca and sugar.
Mix well and let stand for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in large casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: coffee punch
directions: Make coffee and refrigerate.
In punch bowl, add chocolate milk, half and half, sugar and cooled coffee.
Before guests arrive, add scooped ice cream.
Add Kahlua to individual glasses. Great as a winter or summer drink, very rich and serves about 16 to 20 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Separate into small pieces and place in square ovenware dish.
Mix both cans of soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Place evenly over top of soup mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and carrots in margarine until onions are transparent.
Reduce heat and blend in flour; cook until bubbly. Gradually add hot broth, milk, chicken-flavored Rice-A-Roni, diced, cooked chicken or turkey and parsley flakes.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, bell pepper, garlic powder, salt and pepper; drain and cool.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook over high heat, without stirring, until mix reaches 260°.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks.
Pour hot sugar mix in a thin stream over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed.
Add vanilla and continue beating until mixture holds its shape (5 to 10 minutes). Stir in pecans and/or cherries if desired.
Drop by teaspoons. Yields 3 dozen.

title: tropical storm - breakfast drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on medium speed about 1 minute, or until ice is finely crushed.
Serve with your favorite breakfast or just great for a refreshing cool drink.

title: oreo cookie freak out
directions: Crush cookies, set aside 1 cup for topping later.
Press the crushed cookies into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread ice cream in a layer over the cookies.
Top with the fudge.
Sprinkle peanuts over the fudge.
