Cover with cool whip, top with remaining crushed cookies and cherries.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook chicken cut up in 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine all ingredients, including pineapple juice.
On medium heat, cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken; serve over or with rice of your choice.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients all together. Bake in 13 x 9 glass pan (greased) at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: taco dip (pizza style)
directions: Blend until creamy the cream cheese and sour cream.
Use mixer. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons taco seasoning mix.
This is only for look of pizza dough.
Spread the cheese mixture evenly on tray.
Use round tray with small lid on it.
Chill until set.
Combine salsa and taco sauce.
(You may want to strain some of the liquid from salsa so it won't be too liquidy.)
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Grate some Mozzarella cheese on top.
Chill until ready to eat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potato in plain water until done. Mix with oleo, sugar, then flour. Add eggs, then milk. Mix after adding each ingredient. Cook at 325° for about an hour or until done.

title: blue cheese cheese ball
directions: Cream all together. Roll in pecan pieces.

title: general tsao's chicken(china)
directions: Heat the oil in a wok.
Deep fry the chicken, a few pieces at a time, about 1 minute or until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Pour all but 2 Tbsp. of the oil out of the wok.
To the oil in the wok, add the chili peppers, garlic and ginger, stir-fry for 2 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining soy sauce, vinegar, white wine and 1 tsp. cornstarch, mix until smooth. Stir in sugar, sesame oil and salt.
Pour into wok, cook, stirring for 2 minutes until thickened.
Return chicken pieces to wok, mix well and serve.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Place meat in bottom of casserole; add vegetables and cream of mushroom or celery soup with 1/2 can of water.
Stir beef, vegetables, and soup together.
Spread cream of cheddar soup on top.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: low sodium mexican rice
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add rice, green pepper, onion and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, water, sweet basil, oregano and pepper. Cover and simmer until all liquid is absorbed, about 15 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
One serving equals 239 mg sodium.

title: filled and chilled chocolate graham crackers
directions: Break graham crackers into squares.
Ice one square and place another square on top.
Place graham cracker sandwiches in icebox until ready to serve.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Drain fat from pan.
In same pan, cook and stir beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir bouillon cubes in boiling water; stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture.
Cover and cook for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into logs.
Chill and slice. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots.
Fold squash and onion in.
Combine stuffing mix and butter; spread 1/2 in bottom of a 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Spoon vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until heated through.

title: french dressing
directions: In a screwtop jar, combine 1/2 cup salad oil, 2 tablespoons vinegar, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1 teaspoon sugar, 3/4 teaspoon dry mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon paprika and dash of ground red pepper.
Cover and shake well.
Chill.
Shake before serving.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Using an electric mixer, beat together all ingredients except parsley flakes, pimiento and pecans.
When creamy, stir in parsley flakes and pimiento.
Cover and refrigerate until mixture is firm enough to handle.
Shape into a ball and coat with pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve or give as a gift.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Braise pork chops in frying pan.
Place in oblong pan.
Cut up onion and spread over chops.
Mix a little milk in with cream of chicken soup and spread over chops.
Bake (covered with foil) in oven at 375° until pork chops are tender.
Make gravy from soup.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onions and salt. Shape into loaf.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour 45 minutes.
Blend remaining soup, water and 2 to 3 tablespoons drippings.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve with loaf.

title: torte
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped nuts as you would a pie crust. Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Combine pudding and milk as for a pie.
When slightly thickened, add on top.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
Blend 2 packages vanilla pudding, 2 cups milk and whipped topping.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, blend margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix both creamy mixtures together.
In an 8-inch diameter plastic flower pot, layer ingredients in this order:
1/3 of the cookies, 1/2 of the creamy mixture, 1/3 of the cookies, 1/2 of the creamy mixture and cover with the remaining 1/3 of cookies.
Place silk flowers in the center to make it look like a potted plant and keep the secret until serving time.
Serve on dessert plates with a flourish and a clean garden shovel.
Add your own dramatics.

title: beef cabbage casserole
directions: In a large saucepan brown meat and onions.
Remove from heat; add cabbage, carrots, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour rice in 3-quart casserole.
Spoon meat mixture on top.
Pour beef broth and water over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dream cake
directions: First layer:
Mix together the flour, pecans and butter. Press into bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
At medium speed on mixer, add slowly oil, vinegar, lemon juice and celery seed.

title: wassail
directions: Place cloves and cinnamon in a small cloth and tie.
Mix all ingredients; drop in cloth bag of spices.
Heat to boiling and boil 10 minutes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Heat before serving.

title: candied yams
directions: Parboil or bake potatoes until tender.
Peel and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar, orange juice and butter; heat in microwave for 5 minutes.
Pour over the sweet potatoes.
Cook in a 325° oven for 1 hour, or microwave for 30 minutes.
Turn potatoes if top becomes too brown or crusty.

title: broccoli and egg au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine soup and milk. In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, arrange broccoli spears down center of dish, alternating direction of flowerets.
Layer eggs, 1/2 can French fried onions, the soup mixture and cheese over stalks.
Bake covered at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining French fried onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and top with crushed potato chips. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: politician's dessert
directions: Mix together, press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, then crushed cereal.
Reserve 1/3 cup for garnish.
Pat the rest firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° in greased skillet until brown. Wonderful on a cold night with homemade chili and a crisp green salad.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In large pot, mix chicken broth, cream of chicken soups, cream of mushroom and evaporated milk on medium heat.
Mix the chicken in and the fettucini until pasta is separated and al dente.
As it cooks, separate pasta with fork.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange noodles with fork.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Add to chicken mixture and toss well.
Cover and chill.

title: turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of greased 9-inch baking dish.
Top with turkey slices.
In a small bowl, combine soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Pour over turkey.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375°
for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers in blender or with rolling pin.
Mix with melted margarine.
Press into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 375° about 5 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Beat sugar, egg, milk and almond extract.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add melted butter.
Grease and flour (or spray Pam) 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (test with toothpick).
Cool cake on rack.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: aunt peg's chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together in a large casserole. Sprinkle croutons over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or microwave for 8 minutes, then microwave browner for 4 1/2 minutes.

title: fattigmand bakkels
directions: Mix, roll thin and cut with fancy cutter or diamond shapes and fry in deep fat.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Slightly beat eggs in bowl.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add milk, vanilla, butter, pineapple and bread cubes and mix well. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Mix milk, flour and sugar.
Add to melted butter.
Add peaches, but do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in large mixer bowl on high speed until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar, and brown sugar.
Beat in butter.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: veggie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; add sliced zucchini and/or squash 1 minute before end of cooking time. Drain.
In bowl, toss hot pasta and zucchini with artichoke hearts, marinade, olives, sun-dried tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed for recipes; cook onion in butter. Stir in flour and season.
Slowly add milk; cook over low heat until thick.
Mix sour cream, tuna and mushrooms; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: frozen cherry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon. Pour into a plastic container with a lid. Place in freezer. Thaw 1/2 hour before serving.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Measure all dry ingredients, then work in Crisco until it is grainy.
Stir up the vinegar, egg and water together, then pour over other mixture.
Work it together until you can form it into a ball.
After it chills, roll out into 4 or 5 pie shells.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Grind and mix all together; boil for 5 minutes.
Can in hot jars and seal.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, then cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add buttermilk.
Then add dry ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate; will keep several weeks. Makes 5 dozen.
Take amount to be baked and roll out on slightly floured board to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and place on greased cookie sheet; grease top and let sit 1 to 2 hours until they rise.
Place in a preheated oven and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix together the sugar, raisins and pears and let set for one hour.
Stir often so it makes its own juice or liquid.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients to pear mixture.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and stir the ingredients by hand.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine (1 to 1 1/2 sticks) and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press down in a 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.

title: lucious lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, garlic salt, oregano and basil.
In a 2-quart buttered rectangular baking dish, layer 1/3 of noodles, 1/3 of sauce and 1/3 of cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat twice.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: snippy doodle cake
directions: This recipe has been in my family for over 50 years.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in candy bar pieces and dry ingredients.
Now add vanilla and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of cake pan or skillet; add brown sugar, cinnamon and sliced apples.
Combine in bowl oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk, beating by hand as you add.
Sift dry ingredients; add to batter and mix well.
Pour batter onto apple mixture and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting #2
directions: Put all ingredients in top of double boiler. Place over boiling water. Beat with medium speed of mixer about 7 to 10 minutes.
Will stand and hold shape.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion soup; mix.
Drain meat and add picante sauce, then simmer.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream. Layer meat, then cream cheese mixture.
Top with the grated sharp cheese.
Heat in warm oven until cheese has melted.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter or margarine; stir in chunky peanut butter.
Add 1/2 cup coconut and marshmallows.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top.

title: cheese spread
directions: Blend mayonnaise and cheese until smooth.
Blend garlic, onion, and peppers until liquid.
Add to cheese; mix about 2 minutes or until smooth.
Do not over mix.	It will become oily! Can be done in large food processor or in a heavy duty mixer; using a blender for the onion and pepper mixture.
Good with corn chips, crackers or on baked potatoes.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Slice apples; mix with 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Put mixture in pie plate.
Mix crumbs by mixing 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup flour together.
Cut butter into flour and sugar.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.
A bottom crust may be used, if desired.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook frozen broccoli and drain well.
Preheat oven and grease pan.
Mix all the above ingredients together.
Bake in 350 oven for 30 - 40 minutes until done.
Serve hot.
Freezes great.

title: fantasia bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 quart saucepan, melt butter. Remove from heat and stir in crumbs and sugar.
Pat firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Mix coconut and condensed milk together and carefully spread over hot crust.
Bake an additional 12 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes. Spoon melted chocolate chips on top.
Cool until chocolate sets. Cut into small bars.
Makes 48.

title: jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Heat oil in large skillet over medium high heat until hot. Add ham and sausage. Cook and stir 5 minutes or until sausage is lightly browned on both sides. Remove from skillet and place in prepared dish. Place onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in same skillet; cook and stir 3 minutes. Add to sausage mixture. Combine tomatoes with juice, broth, rice, worcestershire sauce, thyme, salt, black pepper and red pepper in same skillet; bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer 3 minutes. Pour over sausage mixture and stir until combined. Cover tightly with the foil and bake 45 minutes or until rice is almost tender. Remove from oven; place shrimp on top of rice mixture. Bake uncovered, 10 minutes or until shrimp are pink and opaque. Makes 8 servings.

title: deep fried duck breast
directions: You can use any kind of duck breast, Mallard, Teal, etc.
Score skin side of breast.
Soak overnight in soy sauce.
Get charcoal grill really hot.
Before grilling breast, put 3 drops of hot sauce on scores of breast and grill.
Grill scored side of breast 1 1/2 minutes and grill other side 1 minute.

title: nancy's whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Drop by small spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Put together with filling in between.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add milk, soup and cheese to sauteed mixture.
After all these ingredients are mixed well, remove from heat and add rice and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Let cool and crumble.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil (or grease from bacon) and cook eggs like scrambled.
Remove from heat.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add rice and stir-fry until heated through.
Add onions and peas and stir-fry for a few minutes.
Add
bacon, eggs and soy sauce. Stir-fry until heated through, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: strawberry cream
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup.
Pour boiling water over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add enough cold water to reserved syrup to measure 1 cup.
Stir into dissolved gelatin.
Chill until almost set.
Prepare dessert topping as package directs.
Beat gelatin until foamy.
Fold Jell-O and strawberries into topping mix.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm; unmold and serve with whipped cream and garnish with strawberries.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place half of crushed potato chips in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine tuna, soup and peas.
Pour into casserole.
Top with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chops and kraut
directions: Drain most of juice from kraut.
Brown pork chops and chopped onions in 1/2 stick butter.
Put kraut in baking dish, then pork chops and sauteed onions.
Pour mushroom soup over all and put onion rings on top.
Bake in 350° oven until chops are tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and put in casserole. Melt cheese in soup and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: apple butterscotch squares
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add apples, nuts and 1/2 of butterscotch morsels.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle remaining butterscotch morsels over the top.
Bake 1 hour or until brown at 325°.

title: lucy gillette's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar until smooth; add eggs alternately with flour and salt; beat well and add flavoring.
Bake in a slow oven for an hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cocoa may be omitted for a plain cake.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine well. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well. Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together on medium heat the sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir quickly to dissolve peanut butter.
Add oatmeal.
Stir until evenly coated.
Drop on waxed paper or cookie sheet and cool.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Coat chicken with butter.
Roll in mixture of crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place in baking dish.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on bottom of pan.
Mix thawed strawberries and syrup with Jell-O; set aside.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add sauce, water, salt and sugar; simmer 2 minutes.

In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour 1/3 meat sauce mixture, then 1/2 uncooked noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce mixture and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Add Parmesan cheese on top. Cover with foil and bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: fiesta rice
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onions, celery and pepper; saute until tender.
Stir in the next 7 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until rice is done.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift cocoa with cake flour mixture. Prepare, bake and cool cake as directed on box.
May top with Chocolate Glaze Frosting.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Slowly heat 1 1/2 cups of the milk, stirring in the brown sugar and salt.
Mix the cornstarch with the remaining milk and add it to the hot milk.
Continue stirring until mixture is thick. Stir in vanilla and spoon into small pudding dishes.
Serves 4.

title: italian vegetable toss
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, olives and onion.
Toss with Italian dressing.
Cover and chill several hours.
At serving time, toss salad with avocado and tomato.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and cayenne if desired.
Stir in the potatoes, cheese, onion, green pepper and ham.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Allow bread dough to thaw.
Saute sliced vegetables.
Flatten each loaf of bread into rectangular shape.
In the center of each rectangle, place layers of ham and salami, then place vegetables and cover with cheese.
Re-fold bread dough back to loaf form. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until loaf is golden brown.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Saute in oil the onion, mushrooms, garlic and pepper.
Add cooked beans and rest of seasoning.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix separately the Ricotta or cottage cheese and yogurt.
Oil casserole.
Layer tortillas, sauce, 3 tablespoons cheese and 3 tablespoons cottage cheese and yogurt.

title: halibut and rice
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine hot bouillon, uncooked rice and seasonings.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with broccoli, 1/2 can French fried onions and Parmesan cheese. Top this with the halibut.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 25 minutes. Stir rice.
Top fish with Cheddar cheese and remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, for 3 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix together squash, onion, peppers and salt.
Let set 1 hour. Drain.
Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, celery, mustard and turmeric.
Add squash mixture to syrup.
Cook 10 minutes after coming back to boil.
Can put in hot jars and seal or let cool and put in plastic freezer boxes and freeze.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put browned hamburger and onions in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over hamburger.
Put Tater Tots on top and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours hours or until brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet, 6 cookies per sheet.
Flour fingers and press down. Sugar tops.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Melt margarine; stir in powdered sugar. Then add Cool Whip. Put a layer of cake in bottom of dish, then Cool Whip mixture. Add another layer of cake, then the rest of Cool Whip mixture. Top with Butterfinger crumbles; refrigerate.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Pour off water and cover with fresh water.
Cook until tender.
Add sugar, mustard, molasses, salt, pepper, onion, salt pork and ketchup.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for about 3 hours.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut wings to make 2 pieces each.
Rinse and dry on paper towel.
Heat oil to 375° in large frypan.
Roll wings in cornstarch, then dip in egg to coat evenly. Deep fry wings until lightly golden brown (about 5 minutes).
Drain on paper towels and place in shallow baking pan. Combine soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, ketchup, salt, jelly and lemon juice in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Stir constantly.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in 1/4 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove meat in large pieces from bone. Also remove skin.
Blend soups and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients except topping.
Place mixture in 2-quart baking dish. Top with crushed crackers or other topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add chocolate, potatoes and lightly beaten egg yolks.
Cream thoroughly.
Add milk, alternately with dry ingredients, then add nuts.
Last, fold in gently the beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 prepared round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For a moist cake, place pan of water in oven while cake is baking.
Use cake filling sprinkled with nuts between cooled layers and frosting to cover all.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together with enough mayonnaise to moisten. (Maybe enough pickle juice to taste.) Salt and pepper to taste. Serve on lettuce leaf or with crackers.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter for 4 minutes.
Add seasonings and add to bread crumbs.
Makes enough to stuff 16 to 20 pound turkey.

title: chocolate velvet dip
directions: Mix together in double boiler and heat until chocolate chips are melted and blended well.
Cool.
Excellent served with assorted fruits.

title: ashford castle brown bread(an irish brown bread)
directions: Preheat a very hot oven-475.
Butter bread pan.
Put the flour into a mixing bowl, add the salt and sift in the baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix the dry ingredients together thoroughly. Melt the butter and honey together and mix with the milk.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture, add all the liquid and mix together quickly but thoroughly with a knife to make a dough. Pour into the butter pan and level off.
Put straight into the preheated oven and immediately reduce the temperature to 350. Bake for about 1 hr. until the loaf is well-risen, nicely browned and shrinking slightly from the pan.
Turn out of the tine for the last minutes of baking and turn upside down to crisp up the base. Cool on a wire rack and use fresh on the day of baking.

title: over that dessert
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over that, pour in the graham cracker crumbs.
Over that, sprinkle the chocolate chips.
Over that, sprinkle the coconut.
Over that, sprinkle the chopped pecans.
Over that, pour the Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Pour milk in double boiler.
Pour in chocolate; stir until blended.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir into mix and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook 10 minutes.
Mix small amount of hot mix with egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mix and cook 2 minutes longer; continue stirring.
Add butter and vanilla. Cover and cool.
Pour into shell.
Top with meringue.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie(my mother's recipe-delicious)
directions: Add all ingredients to milk mixture.
At last, add beaten whites of the 2 eggs.
Pour into crust and bake until puffs and is brown.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Work rice into meat with ketchup until fluffy and set aside. Saute flanken in large pot and add canned tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato soup; season with salt and pepper and add lemon juice. Core cabbage and put into boiling water until leaves loosen. Separate leaves and put small amount of meat mixture into center of each leaf and fold up and place into sauce.
Cook 1 hour, covered.
Add gingersnaps, raisins and apricots and cook another hour, covered.
Add tomatoes and cook another 30 minutes, covered.

title: harvard beets
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and cornstarch together for 5 minutes. Add beets and let stand 1/2 hour or more.
Before serving, heat and add 2 tablespoons of butter.

title: baked potato(low fat)
directions: Slice and remove inside of halves of baked potato.
Combine remaining ingredients and stuff potato skins.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese melts and potato is golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put ingredients in a blender; mix well.

title: creamed eggs
directions: Combine mushroom soup and milk; heat and add sliced eggs to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot over toast or potatoes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt and mix together cheese and oleo.
Add powdered sugar, cocoa, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Press out on a cookie sheet; mash down with hands, but leave thick.
(Mix the powdered sugar and cocoa together before adding to mixture.)
Cut and serve.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Roll out Ritz crackers with rolling pin between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar to egg whites and crackers in a bowl.
Add baking powder, extract and nuts.
Mix together well.
Put in greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top pie with whipped cream.

title: custard filipino style
directions: In a saucepan, caramelize 1/2 cup sugar on a very low flame. Do not burn.
Set aside.

title: apple pie, my eye
directions: Line pie pan with pastry. Sprinkle crumbs onto dough.
Bring sugar, water and cream of tartar to a boil.
Pour over crackers. Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour and meal in a small bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients in a large bowl and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to liquid.
Mix well.
Pour 2 teaspoons of hot grease in iron skillet.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Put kraut in a bowl.
Spread ingredients over top.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator overnight before using.
Toss before serving.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spoon peach (or apple) filling into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Stir together Bisquick, milk, sugar and margarine with fork until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of filling.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cooked chicken, mushroom soup, sour cream and mushrooms. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix the stuffing with the butter and pour in the broth.
Put this mixture on top of the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is bubbly.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream the sugar, egg and butter.
Add the flour, baking soda and sugar.
Stir well.
Add nuts and cherries.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Coat chicken with flour.
Heat oil in a large skillet; add chicken, a few pieces at a time, and brown all sides.
Remove as browned to shallow roasting pan, arranging pieces skin sides up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: seafood creole
directions: Make roux of oil and flour by cooking over low heat until brown; set aside.
Cook all other ingredients in the water about 20 to 30 minutes over low heat.
Gradually add roux and stir until well mixed.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Sprinkle tuna, Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese in pie shell. Sprinkle onions and pimento in pie shell.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over tuna.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: microwave chicken casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, break up chicken into small pieces.
Add soup, water and rice.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 of the onion rings in an 8-inch Corning dish.
Pour chicken mixture over onions.
Microwave on high for 8 minutes (covered).
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add remaining onion rings on top and microwave uncovered for 2 more minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: nut delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put whipped cream on individual pieces.

title: christmas party pinwheels
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and dressing; mix until smooth.
Add red peppers, celery, onion, olives, mix well.
Spread about 3/4 c on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 hours; slice 1/2 inch pieces.

title: cherry nut creme(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 1 3/4 cups milk. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup milk.
Stir into hot pudding until gelatin dissolves.
Cool at room temperature.
Whip the cream, add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into pudding.
Line an 8-inch square baking dish with vanilla wafers crushed and mixed with melted butter.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over wafers.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and half of walnuts and cherries.
Pour over remaining pudding and top with remaining walnuts and cherries.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut in squares and top with whipped cream.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook flour, sugar, salt and milk until thick, using saucepan. Beat eggs, remaining sugar and milk together.
Combine all ingredients and add 3 tablespoons vanilla in ice cream freezer. Add enough milk to fill can 1 1/2 inches from top of can.
Freeze and have fun.

title: spicy chili
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and crushed garlic until beef is brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Stir often.
Cover.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Melt butter and cheese.
Mix together.
Add vanilla.
Pour into jelly roll pan.
Makes lots of fudge.

title: scrambled brunch
directions: Saute ham, onions and mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add eggs and stir until eggs are just set.
Add cheese.

title: honey cornmeal muffins
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in cubes and pour boiling water over, enough to cover.
Let stand while mixing egg, sugar, butter, flour and water. Drain rhubarb; combine with custard.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in moderate oven about 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin fritters(no salt, no sugar)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a large bowl, put pumpkin, eggs, nutmeg, cinnamon, NutraSweet or sugar and dissolved yeast. Mix with mixer at medium speed, add flour a little at a time.
With spatula, stir in raisins.
Cover with foil and let it raise for 30 to 45 minutes.
Put 2-inches of oil in a narrow pot, heat the oil on medium-high.
Drop batter by pushing with your finger from teaspoon, no more than 6 to 7 fritters at a time.
Fry a few minutes until golden on all sides.
Do not make fritters too big. With slotted spoon, take fritters and place on paper towel.
Roll them in sugar or NutraSweet.

title: special crab dish
directions: Clean crabmeat.
Mix wet ingredients, using juice from one lemon.
Mix dry ingredients and pour on top.
Lightly combine.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease pizza pan and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Combine Bisquick and water to make dough.
Roll out and pat into pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Chop chicken.
Drain Veg-All and peas.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Top with the other pie crust.
Make slits on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lo-cal copper pennies
directions: Simmer carrots, onion, bell pepper, tomato sauce, orange juice, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, salt, pepper and sugar in a covered saucepan for 10 to 15 minutes, or until crunchy tender.
(Stir in sugar substitute after removing from heat.)
Serve warm or refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onions, celery and garlic; drain.
Add catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and relish.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve on buns.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil crushed pineapple with sugar and enough water to make 1 cup liquid for 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir well.
Punch holes in hot cake with toothpick. Pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add 1 layer of sliced bananas.
Mix pudding according to package directions and add 1/2 mixture on top of bananas.
Mix the other half pudding with Cool Whip and spread on top of pudding.
Top with chopped pecans and cherries or grated chocolate.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well for 2 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna-rice casserole
directions: Mix soup, water, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour half into greased 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Mix rice, peas and tuna and spread on top.
Add rest of soup mixture. Top with grated American cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peach cobbler i
directions: Melt 1 stick
oleo in small (square) cake pan.
Pour batter over melted oleo; do not stir.
Pour 1 pint (2 cups) fresh fruit, sweetened, over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil and chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat until melted.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder. Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls of dough into bowl of confectioners sugar.
Roll around and shape into a ball.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.
Does not freeze well.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into slices.
Boil in salt water until tender; drain and mash.
Chop onion and saute in margarine. Combine other ingredients and top casserole with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together the Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Fold in fruit and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: bean tostadas
directions: Put oil in a pan.
As soon as it is hot, fry tortilla until crispy, then make sure it is not too greasy.
If it is, wipe it with a napkin or paper towel, then layer some refried beans, lettuce, tomato, cheese and avocado.
Enjoy!

title: bonbons
directions: Use large pan.
Melt margarine; add milk.
Sift in powdered sugar.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans; mix well.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use toothpicks to dip. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler or microwave. Twirl each ball a second to harden dip.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix milk, water and salt together and chill.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Put into freezer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove stems from mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients except oil.
Fill caps with the mixture.
Pour tablespoonful of oil in pan, place mushrooms in pan with stuffed side up.
Pour rest of the oil over mushrooms.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, blending well, forming dough into long tube-like, approximately 1 1/2 to 2-inches in diameter.
Put in wax paper and chill until firm.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground round and onions.
Pour off fat.
Add garlic salt and oregano.
Add pizza sauce.
Put into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can garnish with black olives and green peppers.

title: strawberries dipped in white chocolate
directions: Take the stems out and wash the strawberries.
Pat them dry. Microwave the white chocolate according to package directions. Dip the strawberries, covering them halfway (small end first).

title: chicken breast creamy baked
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and place in greased dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine and pour over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing on top and drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hot french bread sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients, except French bread.
Spread mixture on both sides of French bread which has been split.
Layer your choices of turkey, ham, beef and chicken (deli slices).
Wrap in foil; heat in oven.
Cut and serve.

title: muffin biscuits
directions: Stir together all ingredients. Bake at 400 degrees until browned. Makes 6.

title: oat bran buttermilk waffles
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, oats and oat bran.
Add baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl ,whisk the eggs with the buttermilk just until blended.
Pour mixture over the oat-flour mixture.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add to batter.
Pour some of the batter onto preheated lightly greased waffle iron. Bake waffles until crisp and golden, about 3 minutes on each side. Repeat with remaining batter.
Serve waffles with honey, jam or fruit or berries.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: You may de-ice potatoes in microwave or at room temperature (do not thaw).
Mix all ingredients and pour into a large baking dish.
Top with melted butter and corn flakes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Good for breakfast or dinner.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Melt shortening, brown meat.
Stir in the consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into meat mixture. Serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.
I also use either round or venison steak.

title: pepperoni pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spread marinara sauce evenly over English muffin halves. Sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange 4 pepperoni slices on each half. Broil 4 to 5-inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese bubbles and turns brown.
Cut each muffin half into 4 wedges. Makes 32 servings.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add juice from strawberries and pineapple.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture in mold.
Let congeal.
Add layer of sour cream.
Add remaining Jell-O mixture.
Congeal and enjoy!

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides.
Seal perforations.
Bake for 14 to 19 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper; blend until smooth.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into appetizer size pieces.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 60.

title: rice casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes, then stir and bake 30 additional minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: mildred's cornbread
directions: Mix together and set aside; brown 1 1/2 pounds ground meat and drain.
Chop 1 large onion and 1 jalapeno pepper.
Grate 1/2 pound cheese or use sliced cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter, spread grated cheese, spread ground meat, spread onions/peppers and top with remaining batter in large skillet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sandy's corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute margarine, onion and pepper.
Stir in and pour over corn mixture the sour cream.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Shred Cheddar cheese; sprinkle over top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: melanie's favorite creamy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender.
Chop to small pieces and layer in buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).
Stir 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 8 ounces sour cream and layer.
Crumble Ritz crackers and layer on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, stir together beef, tomatoes and liquid, cabbage and onion.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 3 hours.
Stir in lemon juice and honey. Continue cooking 15 more minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Preheat an oven to 400° (200°C).
Butter standard muffin tins. In a large bowl, stir and toss together the flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl beat the peanut butter briefly until smooth, then beat in a few spoonfuls of the milk.
Beat in the remaining milk then beat in the melted butter and eggs.
Stir in the peanuts.
Add to the combined dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Spoon into the prepared muffin tins, filling each cup about three quarters full.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean, about 15 minutes.
Cool in the tins for 5 minutes, then remove.
Makes about 16 standard muffins.

title: fresh pasta dough
directions: Beat eggs, oil, water and salt together until foamy.
Add enough flour to make a dough that is soft and elastic (much like soft bread dough, but not sticky).
Wrap in a towel; let rest about 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 3 to 4 smaller balls.
Flour and roll through pasta maker; cut as desired.
Or roll very thin with rolling pin on floured surface and cut with sharp knife. Cook in boiling water until al dente.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all above ingredients without their juice.
Use a little grenadine for color.

title: advent bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Lay out soda crackers on foil in a single layer.
Melt the butter and brown sugar until smooth and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips.
When chips are soft, spread and top with chopped nuts.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Dice fine the celery, onion and pepper.
Add butter and cook until clear.
Add mushroom soup and cook until mixed well.
Add milk and a little cornstarch if needed to thicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add lima beans and pimiento.
Simmer a few minutes.
Place in casserole; cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.

title: shrimp with tomato sauce
directions: Remove stems, seed and membranes from chile; chop chile.
Cook and stir chile, onion and garlic in butter in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes, celery, lemon juice, salt, sugar and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir shrimp into tomato sauce; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with parsley.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and add to freezer can.
Fill with regular milk and freeze as usual.

title: salsa
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor.
Chop, but leave coarse.
Use as a dip for nacho chips.

title: creamy parmesan broccoli
directions: To toast pine nuts, spread on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 3 to 6 minutes or until light golden brown, stirring occasionally. Heat oven to 350°. Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain. Place in ungreased 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish or 2-quart casserole. Drizzle with oil. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the cheese; toss to coat.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer rice, chicken and broccoli; pour mixture of soup, milk, cheese and sherry over layers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 minutes in microwave or 1/2 hour at 325° in oven.

title: no-fat oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat yogurt and sugars at medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and oats.
Gradually add to yogurt; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.

title: flambeed bananas foster
directions: *Children usually prefer to omit rum.

title: tutti fruitti (homemade) ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in freezer canister and set in refrigerator until throughly cold, for faster freezing.
Makes about 2 quarts of ice cream.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in double boiler; add milk, egg yolks and margarine or butter.
Cook and stir until thickens. Add coconut and vanilla.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cut zucchini into quarters.
Cook with onions until just tender.
Drain well and then place in baking dish or pie plate. In blender, pour remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over zucchini and onions.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test for being done by inserting knife into center.
If it comes out clean, it is done.
May sprinkle grated cheese over top before serving.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with fork and stir in 1 cup milk. Spread 4 cups of sliced rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar and some cinnamon.
Spread batter over fruit and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and some more cinnamon.
Cover with 1 cup water.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer in dish in order given; chill and serve with nacho chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly in a large bowl.
Add finely chopped onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix in all ingredients; shape into a loaf in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until brown on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake brownies(like candy)
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk in
a large saucepan. Stir well and add margarine.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Boil mixture for 1 minute, then remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla, then mix well.
Add oats.
Stir until oats are well coated. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Pat down with spatula.
Allow to set 15 to 30 minutes. Slice into bars and enjoy!

title: granola
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix last three ingredients.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir. Toast 1 hour at 350°, stirring often.

title: tv critters
directions: Mix oil, dressing, lemon pepper and garlic salt together. Pour over oyster crackers.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: beef lombardi
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion; drain.
Put next 6 ingredients in blender and mix.
Then add to ground chuck and simmer 30 minutes. Cook noodles and drain.
Stir together noodles and sour cream. Spray 13 x 9 dish.
Layer noodle mixture in bottom.
Top with meat mixture.
Top with cheeses.
Cover with foil.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix horseradish and cream cheese together.
Spread on ham slices and roll.
Freeze for about 1 hour.
Take out of freezer and while still frozen, slice each roll into 3 to 4 pieces.
Put into refrigerator until ready to serve. Great hors d'oeuvres.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put rice, sugar, 3 cups milk and salt in top of a double boiler, and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, pour boiling water over raisins and let stand 1/2 hour; drain.
Mix eggs and 1 cup milk with rice and drained raisins.
Put in well-greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Set in pan of hot water to come 1 inch up on the side of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: fried toast
directions: Coat both sides of a slice of bread with margarine.
Fry in a hot skillet until brown.
Serve like a pancake or French toast with syrup, jam or a poached egg.

title: potato casserole
directions: *I like the ones with onions and pepper.

title: old fashion vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Stir in milk. Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes or until custard coats a spoon.
Stirring constantly, mix small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Add to hot mixture and cook 3 minutes longer. Add canned milk and vanilla.
Cool mixture and pour into freezer and freeze.

title: fruit slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Other fruit can be added (i.e., strawberries, peaches, etc.).
Freeze. Serve nearly frozen.
Icy and delicious.

title: diabetic lemon ice cream
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup milk in small saucepan; let soften 5 minutes.
Heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves (about 3 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add Equal and cool.
Prepare whipped topping according to directions, using lemon juice and milk for water.
Whip ten minutes or until thick and fluffy.
Whip egg white until peaks form.
Combine whipped topping and gelatin mixtures and fold in egg white.
Freeze 3 to 4 hours or in electric freezer.

title: date and pecan chews
directions: Spread out thin and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: dad murin's famous spicy pizza sauce
directions: Cut onions, peppers and celery fine.
Cook onions, peppers and celery in shortening (or oil) for 30 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, water and all other ingredients and simmer (slow flame) for one hour.
Use with white crust pizza dough; not as good on whole wheat.
Spread sauce on pizza and sprinkle oregano lightly. Favorite toppings with sauce:
Colby, Cheddar cheese and ham. Usually bake pizza at about 400° for 15 minutes.

title: veal french
directions: Put parsley in egg.
Dip veal in egg, then in flour and repeat once.
In a frying pan with oil, brown veal until a bright gold.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer together over low heat.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Run through food grinder (pepper first).
Drain, saving 3 tablespoons juice.
Soak gelatin in juice and dissolve over hot water.
Add to vegetables.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Leave in refrigerator until spreading sandwiches.

title: english pea salad
directions: Break up lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of pan. Spread english peas over lettuce.
Layer pepper, onion and celery over peas.
Spread mayonnaise over celery.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Best if refrigerated over night.

title: rose's pizza dough
directions: Mix 2 (of a three package set) packages of dry yeast with warm water.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add yeast mixture to other mixture.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Divide into two balls.
Spread on greased pizza pans.
Bade 400 for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and put on sauce, then pizza ingredients.
Bake 10-15 minutes longer.

title: pesto sauce with pine nuts
directions: Combine garlic, basil, pine nuts, half and half and salt in blender.
Blend at low speed until ingredients are chopped fine and form a paste.
Gradually blend in olive oil alternately with cheese, blending until well mixed.
Gradually add whipping cream, stirring until well mixed.
Use as sauce for pasta.
Good on ravioli or on sliced boiled potatoes.
(A little on the firm side, not sliced too thin.)

title: golden grahams
directions: Place whole graham crackers on cookie sheet. Break pecans on top of graham crackers.
Put sugar and margarine in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Cool. Remove with spatula to wax paper to harden.

title: blueberry fluff
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter; fold all together.
Put on crust. Cover with blueberry pie filling; refrigerate.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Trim brisket of all visible fat.
Make a thin paste of remaining ingredients, using enough liquid smoke for a spreadable consistency (about 1/2 cup).
Rub mixture over entire brisket; place on a sheet of aluminum foil large enough to cover and seal completely.
Place in a baking pan large enough to catch any drippings.
Bake in a 250° oven overnight or 6 to 8 hours.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes before slicing.
This is easier to slice using an electric knife.
Slice across the grain of the meat.

title: german nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt, walnuts and raisins.
Lastly add 2 cups of milk; mix well. Put into buttered loaf pan or 2 small ones.
Let stand 20 minutes, then bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Makes delicious sandwiches with cream cheese.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut all four edges off bread slice.
Cut bread without edge into 6 sticks.
Put sticks and edges in pan and bake for 30 minutes in 200° oven until lightly toasted brown and hard.
Remove from oven.
Take bread sticks and stir around in peanut butter; mix until covered.
Place on foil.
Take edges and crumble up over top of peanut butter sticks.
They are now ready to eat.

title: dirty rice
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add ground beef and all vegetables, except parsley and scallions.
Brown beef and then turn the heat to low.
Cook for about 45 minutes, stirring often.
Add 2 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and reduce the heat.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add green onion and parsley.
Cover and cook another 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients (except last 2) and shape into a loaf in 2 qt. casserole dish. Cook on high for 20 minutes, rotating every 5 minutes until time is up. Mix the catsup and Worcestershire sauce and spread over top of meat loaf. Heat for 1 minute.

title: chicken chip bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except shredded cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese, then with potato chips.
Bake at 425° until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chopped walnuts (optional). Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on cooled cake.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and pepper with 1/2 cup salt and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and cover with the sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil and can immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: cheese bars
directions: Mix grated cheese and butter well with mixer.
Add flour; mix well.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Shape in small balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Top with pecans; bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Delicious with all kinds of fresh fruit.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Saute leeks and onion in butter until yellow.
Add potatoes, carrot, chicken stock and salt.
Bring to a rapid boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer until potatoes and carrots are soft.
Mash and rub through a fine sieve.
Return to heat and add milk. Season to taste and cool.
Add cream and chill thoroughly.
Serve with a sprinkling of finely chopped chives.

title: cheese twists
directions: Unfold one of the pie crusts and press the lines from the fold.
(Use a floured rolling pin.)
Roll out pie crust to a 12 inch square.
Trim dough to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Brush with 1 tablespoon of the margarine and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese.
Cut dough crosswise into 12 (1-inch) strips. Fold each strip in half lengthwise and pinch edges together. Twist.
Place twist about 1-inch apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden. Cool on baking sheets.
Repeat with remaining pie crust.
Makes 24.

title: apple and butternut squash soup
directions: Cut squash in half, seed and peel.
Peel, core and coarsely chop the apples.

Peel and coarsely chop the onion or put all in blender and chop. Combine all ingredients with herbs, broth, water, bread, salt and pepper in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer 45 minutes. Puree in blender, filling only 1/4 full at a time. Return soup to saucepan and bring just to a boil. Add cream and serve at once.

title: curry dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Combine all.
Chill.
A party favorite surrounded by sliced mushrooms, cucumbers, carrots, cauliflower, radishes, bell peppers and cherry tomatoes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onion, carrot and celery in salted water.
Use only enough water to almost cover.
Boil until water is cloudy and vegetables are soft.
Add Velveeta and stir until melted.
Add salt, pepper, butter and milk.
Heat slightly; do not boil.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Melt butter and cheese in pan over low heat.
Simmer about 20 minutes, stirring frequently; cool.
Whip cream and mix with the cheese mixture.
Trim crust of bread, cut in half, and then cut lengthwise in thirds.
Cut again into squares, measuring about 1 1/2-inches.
Place bread cubes in mixing bowl and pour cheese over the bread.	Lightly mix in order to coat the bread with the cheese mixture.
Spread bread cubes on foil lined cookie sheets. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
This also can be frozen and baked at a later date.
Serve warm.	Yields 6 dozen.

title: green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a covered dish for 3 hours at 350°.

title: raw relish
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and salt, stirring occasionally.
Mix the rest in the vinegar mixture.
Let stand 3 or 4 hours.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and melted fat.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until light.
Add melted chocolate, then the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Then add to the batter alternately with the buttermilk, beating well.
Fold in pecans and coconut.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(I bake in 3 pans until done, about 25 minutes.)

title: wieners on potatoes
directions: Crem Irish potatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Boil wieners until tender, place on potatoes.
Bake 15 minutes oven about 425°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all.
Place in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: lye soup
directions: Dissolve the Borax in 1 cup hot water. Stir well. Dissolve lye in cold water. Add grease and other ingredients.
Pour into granite flat pan.
Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: chicken pillows
directions: Pound chicken breasts with meat pounder until flat and about the same thickness.
Lay a slice of ham on each one.
Divide cheese and place on top of ham.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon bread crumbs on top of each.
Roll chicken from wide end.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place in casserole dish.
In a small pan, melt margarine and add cooking wine.
Pour this over chicken pieces. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oscar's kitty cookies
directions: Allow cheese and margarine to become room temperature.
Mix together adding garlic and flour.
Add enough milk to help form into a ball.
Chill 1 hour.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, margarine and cinnamon until it looks like coarse cornmeal.
Place apples in an oblong dish (about 9 x 13-inch) and cover with flour and sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° until well browned or until apples are tender.
Can top with Cool Whip.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add green pepper and chopped onion and cook until tender, not brown.
Stir in cans of soup, water and bouillon cube.
Heat to boiling, then turn down heat.
While sauce cooks, make meat balls.

title: pineapple angel pie
directions: Bring to a boil the water, sugar and pineapple, then thicken with the cornstarch. When cool, add the two beaten egg whites. Fill baked pie shell and top with whipped cream sweetened with powdered sugar and vanilla. Chill in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine in a large mixing bowl.
Mix with fork until blended. Shape into balls of desired size.
Brown in the 2 tablespoons oil.
When browned, add the soup, diluted with an equal quantity of milk.
Simmer, stirring frequently.
Serve over hot, cooked and drained noodles.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup of nuts and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples, then place on baking sheet.
Fill apples with sugar.
Top with butter.
Bake apples until tender and lightly browned.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan and add milk.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Slowly stir small amount of the mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Return this mixture to saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Take off of stove and add vanilla and butter.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue. (Beat the egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.)
Brown slightly.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar 1 teaspoon at a time. Add salt. Add nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla. Mix together. Preheat oven to 350°. Cover cookie sheet with foil and drop cookies by teaspoons 1-inch apart. Put in oven. Turn off heat. Let sit overnight. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: * loco chili *
directions: Crumble beef into heated skillet and cook over moderate heat until meat loses red color.
Add onion during the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain off grease.
Add corn, chili and seasoning mix.
Mix well and simmer, covered, while preparing biscuits.

title: apricot bites
directions: Boil dried apricots 1 minute.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix cream cheese, onion and chutney or marmalade until well blended.
Fill apricot halves.
Dip in nuts.

title: fresh fruit pudding compote
directions: Pour milk and juice into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with hand beater or electric mixer on lowest speed for 1 minute. Add 1 cup of Cool Whip and beat 1 minute longer.
Set aside.

title: mary ellen and natalie's dormitory turkeys
directions: Ice an Oreo with chocolate icing.
On top of icing, line candy corns in semi-circle.
Use a Hershey Kiss and put it in the center.
Dab a small amount of icing on the top of the Kiss and then put a red hot in it.

title: cherry squares
directions: Press into 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Do not bake.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in baking dish; sprinkle sugar.
Add water. Sprinkle Jell-O and cake mix; add melted margarine.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: imagination cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, Jell-O and wine together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into well-greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Divide into 2 containers; freeze!
Two hours before ready to serve, take from freezer.
When ready to serve, add 32 ounces of 7-Up to each punch bowl.

title: sweet potatoes and ham
directions: Peel and slice in 1/4-inch slices the sweet potatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with ham and then cover with apples and sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are done.

title: french peas
directions: In a saucepan, cook onions and lettuce in oil over low heat for 5 minutes. Set aside. Combine flour with water; add to onion mixture and cook, stirring until thickened. Add peas, water chestnuts and seasoning.
Heat through and serve.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cook sauce on top of the stove (bring to a boil).
Let the mixture cool.
Dip each piece of chicken into the sauce and place in pan lined with aluminum foil.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; add Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and coloring.
Pour into crust.
In mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar to soft peaks. Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Spread on pie; seal to edge.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.

title: thin white sauces
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk.
Heat to boiling over direct heat and then boil gently 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Makes 1 cup sauce, then boil gently 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: sweet blueberry muffins
directions: To prepare batter, combine eggs, milk and oil in a bowl.
In separate bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20 muffins.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Mix cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven.
Poke holes in cake.
Pour coconut cream on top of hot cake.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Add oil.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Now add zucchini.
Mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour ingredients into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add flour to shortening; add salt and blend together until crumbly.
Beat egg lightly in some of the water.
Work into the flour mixture; add vinegar and blend all together lightly.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Will make 3 single crusts or 2 double crusts.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the hamburger with the onion, salt and pepper to taste and the chili powder; drain.
Put in bottom of casserole.
Next add the corn and peas and carrots or green beans.
Cover with the mashed potatoes.
Put in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Melt butter; add flour, mustard, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Add milk and cook until thickened. Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted. Add egg and cook 3 minutes. Serve on toast. Sprinkle with paprika. Yield: 10 servings.

title: atsyomo(twisted cakes; african)
directions: Beat the egg in a deep bowl.
Add the sugar, nutmeg and anise seed.
Beat well.
Sift the flour, salt and baking powder.
Knead well, adding more flour if the dough is too sticky.
Roll out on a floured board with a floured rolling pin, to slightly less than 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 1-inch strips, then cut on an angle, making diamond shapes.
Cut a slit in each and pull a corner through.
Or use the unslit diamond shape.
Fry in deep hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll in sugar. (Makes 6 dozen cakes.)

title: quick "fruit cake" cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Make a batter of the flour, egg, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Stir in vanilla.

title: holiday potato dish
directions: Remove	skin
from potatoes and shred into bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Remove from heat.	Stir in soup and
sour
cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese; mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover.
Refrigerate
overnight. Drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for
hour. Garnish
with pimento and parsley.	Serves 12.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook first five ingredients for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and spoon onto waxed paper.
Let harden and cool.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Combine and boil 2 minutes.
Place graham crackers on cookie sheet or long pan.
Spoon mixture over grahams and bake 12 minutes.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine everything except nuts in top of double boiler.
Place over simmering water.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix. Spread quickly into buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool and cut. Makes 2 dozen.

title: rigatoni
directions: Cook meat until brown.
Boil rigatoni with large onion until tender; drain and place in large pan with meat and cheese.
Pour sauce over this and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix with mixer.
No special order.
Put in large greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: eunice's veg-beef soup
directions: Cut beef in bite size pieces, brown in skillet with small amount of oil.
In large pot, mix tomatoes (cut up), green beans, corn, potatoes, onions and carrots.
Add browned beef and V-8 juice.
Bring to boil, turn down to medium.
Cover and let simmer for 45 minutes.

title: heather's dip
directions: Layer sour cream, salsa, jalapenos and cheese.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Soak poppy seed in boiling water while mixing the rest of the cake.
Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, sour cream, sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add coconut, then poppy seed and water.
Pour into tube pan; bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Loosen gently; invert on plate.
Top with following:

title: chestnut stuffing with sausage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onions and cook over medium heat until soft.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl; add chestnuts.
Cook sausage in same skillet until brown, breaking up with a fork.
Remove most of the fat.
Add sausage to chestnut mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Makes about 5 (1/2) cups.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375, sift together and set aside the flour, baking soda, and salt. Stir together margarine, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, and water. Beat in 1 egg, as listed above. Add the flour mixture and mix well. Stir in the 1/2 C of chopped nuts. Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle over top of batter the 6 oz package of semi sweet chocolate morsels. Place in 375° oven for 1 minute. Remove pan from oven and run knife through the batter to marbleize. Return to oven and continue to bake for 12 to 14 minutes. Cool. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: carne asada
directions: Blend in a saucepan. Cook on low.
Marinate meat 48 hours.

title: kick the can ice cream
directions: You will need 1 (1 pound) empty clean coffee can and 1 (3 pound) empty clean coffee can.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Blend all in blender for 1 min, scrape sides, blend 30 seconds more.
Refrigerate 2-3 hours to develop flavor.
Much better than store bought sauce.
Makes approximately 1 1/4 cups.

title: microwave candy bar fudge
directions: Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with foil and set aside.
In a bowl, microwave on High margarine or butter, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in cocoa, brown sugar and milk.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil, stirring once.
Stir again.
Cook for 1 minute more.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread into pan.
In a glass bowl, combine caramels and 1 tablespoon water.
Cook, uncovered, on 50% power for 4 to 5 minutes or until melted, stirring once.
Stir in nuts and spread over fudge.
In a 2-cup glass measure, cook chocolate on Medium for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until melted, stirring once. Spread atop caramel.
Chill until firm.
Remove from pan and cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 64 pieces.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute beef and onion until brown.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Add a small amount of water or juice if necessary.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Cover with Shake and Bake or any seasoned coating.
Fry in hot fat until brown.
Serve hot.

title: quick food processor pie dough
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add flour and salt.
Top with cover and process, pulsing 3 or 4 times or until combined.
Cut butter into 6 pieces; add to flour mixture, pulsing 5 or 6 times or until mixture resembles coarse meal.
With processor running, slowly add water, a teaspoon at a time, until dough forms a ball, leaving the sides of the bowl.
Cover and chill dough for 30 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness and fit into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drink 4 ounces a day.
Good for what ails you.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Melt peanut butter; pour over corn flakes.
Mix well.
Grease cookie sheet.
Spread in mixture.
Melt chocolate chips; pour over peanut butter and corn flakes.
(Pour smooth.)
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into chunks.
Dip in soy sauce and then in flour. Cook thoroughly in pan with oil.
In a wok or clean frying pan, cook frozen vegetables according to package directions; drain excess water.
Add sweet and sour sauce.
Add drained pineapple. Add pork.
Cook on medium heat until thoroughly heated.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix and freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: s'mores
directions: Butter 9-inch square pan.
Heat syrup and margarine to boiling in 3-quart saucepan; remove from heat.
Add chocolate and vanilla. Stir until chocolate melts.
Fold in cereal until completely coated.
Fold in marshmallows.
Turn into pan and press.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 2 hours.

title: deep dish meat pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Roll pastry into a 12-inch circle.
Cover and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, cook potato and onion in margarine over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 5 to 6 minutes or until onion is tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, herb and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add broth all at once.
Stir in peas and carrots.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in meat.

title: tabouli
directions: Add all ingredients together and toss.
A food processor is most handy here.

title: ham roll-up
directions: Put almonds on cookie sheet.
Broil until brown.
Crush severely!
Combine all ingredients, except ham.
Spread on ham slices and roll up.
Place in freezer until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and serve at room temperature.

title: banana nut bread #1
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add bananas, flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts; mix well. Bake in one large loaf or 3 small loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
