directions: Mix chopped apples with 1 cup sugar and let stand 30 minutes. Mix dry ingredients together; add apple mixture, oil and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.

title: zucchini bisque
directions: Saute onion and butter or margarine.
Simmer zucchini and chicken stock for 15 minutes (covered).
Puree 1/2 of zucchini mixture with 1/2 of onion mixture while slowly adding cream and spices.
(Repeat with other half.)
Serve hot or cold.
Also great with cauliflower.

title: peanut butter swirls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips. Spread in greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle chips on top. Place in 350° oven for 3 minutes. Remove and run knife through to swirl. Return to oven for 15 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: 1940's wartime cake
directions: In a pot boil brown sugar, 1 1/2 cups water, vegetable shortening, raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves for 3 minutes. Cool completely.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Dissolve salt and baking soda in 2 teaspoons water.
Add to cooled mixture.
Blend in flour mixed with baking powder.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake 50 minutes. Don't need to refrigerate.
Store tightly covered up to 1 month.
Able to be mailed.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and mix in shortening. Gradually add the warm water.
Mix very gently.
Knead until dough is soft to handle.
Cover and let dough rise for about 20 minutes. Roll into golf ball size pieces.
Flatten with hands and make hole in center.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix ingredients and let set.

title: muffins for diabetics
directions: *If you use self-rising flour, omit the baking powder and salt.

title: new orleans gumbo
directions: Fry salt pork in heavy skillet until crisp.
Add flour to slightly thicken and make a roux (gravy).
Pour mixture into a large kettle of water.
Add cut up chicken, ham and sausage.
Cook until chicken is done.
Add celery, tomatoes and onion.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add okra, crab legs and shrimp.
Cook until okra is tender.
Add file powder.
Serve over hot, steaming rice.

title: dry beef dip
directions: Cut top off bread and hollow out saving the pieces of bread from inside.
Mix all the ingredients by hand; cut dry beef in pieces.
Put into bread; put top on and cover with foil. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until warm. Serve using bread pieces.

title: mexican sandwiches
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salsa, chili powder and olives.
Heat and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Cut open the hard rolls and haul a cavity out.
Fill with meat sauce; close and wrap individually in foil.
Serve or may be refrigerated and reheated in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add green beans, tomatoes, onions, celery and carrots.
Add tapioca and seasonings.
Mix slightly together.
Add 5 potatoes, quartered if large.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°. Do not add any water.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake per package directions. Mix sugar and cocoa. Add water and marshmallows. Stir until mixed well. Pour into a 13 x 9 pan. Spoon already prepared cake over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes. All ovens are different, check on the cake starting after 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix egg, beef and soup mix together.
Stir in stuffing mix and add pepper and onion.
Do not add salt, as the soup mix is salty.

title: bean dip
directions: In a cake pan, spread the beans.
In a bowl, mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread over refried beans.
Chop onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Put over top, then put the 2 cheeses on top.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Eat with tostada chips.

title: tuna treats(kids love them)
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into 6 buttered muffin tins. Sprinkle 1/4 cup grated cheese on top of each muffin.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding(mother's recipe)
directions: In saucepan, mix together the cocoa and flour until smooth; add milk and sugar and cook until scalded.
Add beaten eggs, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sugar.	Blend thoroughly.

title: pecan balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt, sugar and pecans.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350°.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and add taco seasoning. Warm refried beans on medium heat while cooking hamburger meat. Put a layer of tortilla chips on bottom of deep casserole dish. Next, layer hamburger meat, shredded cheese, chips, more shredded cheese, refried beans, chips, salsa and Cheez Whiz. Place in oven at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: never fail pie crust(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening. Add the egg, vinegar and cold water.
Roll as thin as you like. This is enough for 2 double 9-inch pies.
If you want to cook, bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix with pudding. Add all other items. Beat 5 minutes. Pour into buttered pans which have been sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon. Let stand for 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Check; it may take another 10 minutes. If baked in glass pans, bake at 325° until golden brown. Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 large pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together dry pudding mix and crushed pineapple with juice. Add Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots until tender; drain.
Combine soup, sugar, salad oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour hot mixture over carrots, green pepper and onion rings.
Chill overnight.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix
well
over popped corn and spread on a cookie
sheet.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart microsafe cup on High power for 30 to 60 seconds.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Whisk in milk. Microwave on High power for 3 to 5 minutes, until mixture thickens, whisking every 2 minutes to combine.
Stir in cheese; blend well.
Microwave on High power for 30 seconds, if needed, to melt cheese.
Snap off tough ends from asparagus.
Wash in cold water.
Pour 1/4 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon salt into 12 x 8-inch microsafe dish.
Place 1 pound asparagus spears in dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High power for 6 minutes, rearranging halfway.

title: diabetic punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, Kool-Aid and Sweet 'N Low. Freeze. When ready to serve, slightly thaw. Add 7-Up or ginger ale. Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add half of the skim milk, stirring steadily, to the boiling point.
Mix in sugar, then cook on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining milk.

title: coffee sherbet
directions: Combine sugar, gelatin, coffee powder and salt in saucepan. Stir in 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 6 cup refrigerator tray.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Remove to chilled mixer bowl.
Break into chunks.
Beat until smooth but still mushy.
Return to tray, cover and freeze until firm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: valley trash
directions: Put crackers in large bowl.
Pour oil and stir well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Can be frozen.

title: all day beef stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees.
Dump all ingredients into large oven proof pan.
Cover.
Cook in 250 degree oven 7 hours or 300 degree oven for 5 hours.
Stir a couple times during cooking if you get the chance.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk slowly.
Cook over medium-high heat until thick and smooth stirring constantly. Stir in vanilla and butter.

title: raspberry brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well. Gradually add sugar. Beat chocolate mixture into eggs. Add raspberry liqueur.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients. Add nuts. Pour in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Drop small quantities of raspberry jam in center of each square to be cut. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan before cutting.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dump cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix in medium bowl the flour, milk, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Place "gently" the fruit on top and pour juice over.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Bake at 370° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with 8 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in order listed.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: ham-macaroni bake
directions: Stir macaroni into a large amount of boiling water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse at once.
Stir in soup, milk, onion, ham and half of the cheese.
Spoon into buttered 6-cup baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat the pear juice to boil; dissolve the gelatin in it. Cool.
Mix in cream cheese and 2 tablespoons cream.
Add mashed pears and cheese to the gelatin mixture, then add the whipped cream.
Put into oiled mold.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Place in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients except breadcrumbs, stirring well.
Spoon mixture over chicken, top with breadcrumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced plums
directions: Wash and dry plums.
Place them in a stone jar or bowl.
Boil vinegar, sugar and spices together for 10 minutes.
Pour over plums.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain off the liquid and bring to a boil.
Add to plums and cook until plums are clear, but not broken.
Pack in clean, hot Ball jars, filling with pickling syrup.
Seal immediately.
The plums should retain their color and should be firm and plump in appearance.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine corn, eggs and onion.
Mix well. Combine flour, salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir into corn mixture. Add cream, butter and pimientos.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared baking dish. Set dish in pan and pour hot water to 1-inch depth around dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/4 hours or until pudding is firm when knife is inserted in center. Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets until tender.
When cool enough to handle beets, remove skin and short tops.
Slice and pack in warm jars.
Boil together vinegar, water, sugar and cinnamon; pour over sliced beets and seal.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place drained peaches in greased 8 x 8 inch pan.
Melt butter - mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees until crust is brown and inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add all together and mix with dressing.
It's better if it sets overnight before eating.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into a small casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Dissolve brown sugar and salt in water; add syrup.
Cook, without stirring, to hard ball stage.
Pour gradually over egg whites that have been beaten stiff.
Beat constantly.
Add vanilla and continue beating until cool.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: seafood cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, then chill in icebox.
Allow one fourth cup of shrimp, lobster or crab meat or three oysters to each serving.
Chill fish in icebox, then place in cocktail glasses and add sauce.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with whole graham crackers, making sure edges touch.
Mix pudding and milk on low speed for two minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over graham crackers.
Top with graham crackers as for bottom.
Spread frosting on top and let set for five minutes.
Refrigerate.
Serves 18.

title: april's awesome lasagna
directions: Cook 8 noodles in salted water.
Add 1 teaspoon of oil to prevent sticking.
Drain and let cool.
Brown beef.
Add onion powder, garlic, oregano, parsley flakes and Italian seasoning. Drain fat, then add tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Place 4 noodles in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of meat sauce and half of cheese over the noodles.
Repeat noodles, meat sauce and cheese. Top generously with Parmesan cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Fry hamburg and onion.
Drain off grease.
Put in tomato soup, yellow wax beans and green beans.
Simmer together for 20 minutes. Make mashed potatoes.
Put on top of hamburg mixture in a casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked limas with tomato sauce
directions: Cook beans in water until tender.
Drain and pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook bacon until it begins to brown.
Add celery, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender and bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over limas. Stir gently.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: gretchen smith's sweet pickled peaches
directions: Bring the first 4 items to a boil.
Put seasoning in each quart jar.
Drop about 2 quarts of peaches into boiling mixture and cook about 3 minutes after they come to a boil.
Take out of hot liquid hurriedly.
Do not overcook.

title: hershey cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 6 days (if you can) before cutting.

title: krispy pepper biscuits
directions: Put flour in a large bowl or kettle.
Make a well and add warm water, yeast, oil and seasonings.
Mix well, adding more flour if necessary.
Knead dough until as smooth as bread dough.
Let rise until double.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Mix chicken, stuffing and mayonnaise together.
Stuff into cooked shells.
Mix soups together.
Spread some on bottom of baking dish.
Arrange shells in dish, stuffing side up.
Pour soup mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Saute green onions and bell pepper in margarine until tender.
Add Ro-Tel and amount of water on rice directions.
Add rice, seasoning and sausage.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until desired thickness.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; cool slightly.
Add other ingredients and mold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut the cooked chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Combine chicken, broth and soup mixture together in casserole dish. Prepare stuffing according to package directions and spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients.
Then add the rest of the ingredients to this mixture.
Simmer.
May need to add more milk if the soup becomes too thick.

title: old fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and spices.
Toss in blueberries to coat.
In a smaller bowl, combine eggs, milk and butter.
Stir these into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with almonds and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 20 to 21 muffins.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding mix and crushed pineapple.
Add cottage cheese, walnuts and marshmallows.
Fold in topping.
Refrigerate overnight.
Delicious.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain fruit well.
I prefer lite mix in oleo, brown sugar and curry.
Two tablespoons cornstarch that is mixed with sugar and curry.
Mix all together.
Let set overnight.
Bake next day for 1 hour at 325°.

title: kansas chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift flour and other ingredients together and all alternately with milk.
Cook in 3 layers at 350°.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add sour cream and walnuts.
Add baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Batter is thick.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a tube pan or 30 minutes in an oblong pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar after it cools.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until fudge balls up when dripped in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth and beginning to thicken.
Pour into a buttered plate.
Let cool and harden.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken elegance
directions: Place boneless chicken breasts in baking dish, spread with mayonnaise and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: donna bell's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender, but firm.
Cool, peel and slice into bowl.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble into potatoes.
Cook diced onion in bacon fat until light brown and tender.
Add onions and 3 tablespoons bacon fat to potatoes.

title: weeknight fajitas
directions: In a large bowl, pour dressing over chicken, green bell pepper, onion, garlic and oregano.
Toss lightly.
Refrigerate at least 10 minutes.
Drain. Stir-fry chicken mixture until chicken is browned and no longer pink.
Stir in tomatoes.
Wrap tortillas in dampened paper towels.
Microwave on High (100%) for 45 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until softened.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture.
Serve with salsa, sour cream, shredded cheese, refried beans or guacamole.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer half of the bread cubes and half of the cheese cubes. Push down into melted butter in pan. Brown sausage and sprinkle over top.
Add the drained mushrooms.
Layer remaining bread cubes and cheese cubes.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over bread mixture.
Sprinkle with dry mustard. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese oven baked chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in melted butter.
Mix the dry ingredients together.
Dip the chicken in this mixture.
Place in a single layer in a pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shoo-fly pie(a pennsylvania dutch favorite)
directions: Put 1/2 of crumb mixture (flour, sugar, butter and baking powder) in each shell. Pour 3/4 juice mixture (molasses, hot water and baking soda) in each shell. Pour 1/2 of remaining juice mixture over each shell. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate impossible pie
directions: Process all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: clubhouse salad
directions: Mix all together. Best if chilled in refrigerator for an hour before serving.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Bring to a rapid boil the oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour over the dry ingredients while hot; stir well and add the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in a large cookie sheet with sides and bottom, greased and floured, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook the icing while the cake is baking.
Put on while the cake and icing are hot.

title: venison surprise
directions: Brown ground venison and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Combine meat with Ragu sauce in large pot.
Cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: black-eyed pea stew
directions: Drain the black-eyed peas and place them in a medium-size heavy saucepan together with the onion, carrots, tomatoes, savory, marjoram, red pepper flakes, bay leaves and cinnamon stick.
Add the water, stir to mix, place over moderately high heat and bring to a boil; about 3 minutes.
Lower the heat so that the mixture bubbles gently, partially cover and simmer until the peas are tender, about 50 minutes.
Mix in the corn, black pepper and salt and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Discard the bay leaves and cinnamon stick.
Before serving, top each portion with 1/3 cup of the yogurt.

title: old time spice cake
directions: In medium bowl, with electric mixer, beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Beat in soup.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and cloves; add to soup mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture, beating at low speed until well combined.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool cake in pans for 10 minutes and then remove to wire rack.

title: sausage balls(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Combine all in a large bowl.
Mix with hands until all biscuit mix is absorbed.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: crab stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Thinly slice tops and bottoms from tomatoes.
Remove pulp from stem end; drain.
In small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Use to fill tomatoes.
Cover and chill.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into very small pieces.
Mix other vegetables together with cauliflower.
Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese well together.
Stir in vegetables.
Bacon bits can be added if desired.
The longer this sets, the better it tastes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix and pour into shell.
Refrigerate.
One half cup lemon juice may be used instead of lemonade.

title: broccoli-chicken bake
directions: Boil chicken on stove top for 1 hour; cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
On bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan, put chicken and broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise and cream of mushroom soup together. Pour over top of chicken and broccoli; mix.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add margarine, cream cheese, sour cream and salt.
Beat until combined.
Put in buttered ovenproof bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: island fruit kabobs
directions: Sprinkle slices of banana, avocado and papaya in lemon juice to coat.
Alternate the fruit on 5 to 7-inch skewers.
Stick skewers in a pineapple with top intact or serve on a plate garnished with greens.
Serve with bowl of homemade or bottled papaya seed dressing.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In small saucepan, combine chocolates and coffee.
Heat over low heat until chocolates are melted.
Cool.
In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs and yolks on high speed 10 minutes.
Add sugar and beat until shiny, 5 minutes.
Add melted chocolates, rum and vanilla.
Beat just until thoroughly blended.

title: microwave jelly
directions: In 3-quart casserole, blend together juice and pectin.
Stir in water.
Cover.
Microwave on High 8-9 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes, until bubbles form around edge of dish.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Cover.
Microwave on High 6-8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes, until mixture boils.
Then, time for 1 minute of boiling.
Stir and skim off foam with metal spoon.
Ladle into prepared glasses.
Seal.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refreeze.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion.
Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil; add 1 cup oil and return to boil.
Pour over cabbage and onion. Refrigerate and let stand overnight.

title: homemade "reducing" diet for dogs
directions: Cook beef.
Drain fat and cool. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Yields 1 3/4 pounds.
Keep refrigerated.

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: Cook carrots, boiling 5 minutes until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, juice and ginger.
Pour over carrots and toss.
Add garnish.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn and peanuts in a large bowl.
Combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and water in a separate microwavable soft glass bowl.
Microwave on High for a total of 9 to 11 minutes, stirring once every five minutes.
Add baking soda at end of cooking time and stir.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir to coat.
Spread on foil to cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool. Top with applesauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. In another bowl mix eggs, oil, vanilla, and pineapple. Combine dry ingredients with egg mixture. Add nuts and carrots. Bake in two (2) round 8 inch cake pans. Bake at 275° until tooth pick comes out clean. Cool before frosting.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a very large container. Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Mix well to coat.
Bake at 250° in a large roaster pan for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add chocolate and mix well.
Add eggs and beat for 5 minutes on high speed. Fold in 4 ounces of Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Spread additional 4 ounces of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with toasted almonds or crushed Heath bars if desired.

title: country breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine rest of ingredients together and mix well.
Pour over bread; refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: margarita slurpees
directions: In a blender container, combine all ingredients.
Add ice last to fill container.
Blend at high speed until slurpee consistency. Enjoy!

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill the bottom of an unbaked pie crust with chopped rhubarb.
Pour the egg mixture over the rhubarb.
Cover with pie crust crumbs mixed with sugar and cinnamon.

title: peanut butter oatmeal chewies
directions: Beat peanut butter, sugar and butter until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well. Chill dough, about 1 hour.

title: overnight potato soup
directions: Place sliced potatoes in a large bowl.
Add cheese.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese; mix well.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle corn flakes; drizzle 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: plum good cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon and cloves together.
Add flour and plums last.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: holly taters
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Soak potatoes in water; drain and coat well with flour mixture.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in pan.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Turn potatoes one time during baking.

title: tabbouleh salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; let stand 30 minutes. Drain well and cool.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Just before serving, stir in tomatoes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: orange pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice and chill slightly to thicken some, then beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add sugar and whipped cream.
Pour into vanilla wafer crust.
Chill until firm.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and spread on top. Cool and cut into bars.

title: meaty cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese; add Ro-Tel and then add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Serve with chips.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix 1 stick of butter (at room temperature) with cracker crumbs.
Make a crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.

title: cottage cheese potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and dice, chill. Combine all remaining ingredients; toss with chilled potatoes. Refrigerate. Will be good for several days.

title: crab or shrimp pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine baking mix, 1 cup of cheese, milk and 1/2 of the melted butter in a medium bowl; mix together by hand until well mixed.
Pat out the dough into a circle approximately 8-inches in diameter, with a slight lip around the edge.
Sprinkle the parsley over the top of the dough.
Sprinkle the crab or shrimp over parsley.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over crab or shrimp.
(Don't go to the edges, leave about 1/2-inch around crust.)
Bake for 14 to 16 minutes until cheese is slightly brown.
Mix remaining butter and garlic powder and brush over the top as soon as it comes out of the oven.
Slice and serve warm.

title: church window candy
directions: In saucepan, put chocolate bits and butter.
Cook over low heat until chocolate melts; cool.
Stir in colored marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
Divide mixture in half.
Shape in 6-inch log. Roll in remaining walnuts.
Wrap in clear plastic.

title: taco dip
directions: Chill a pie plate.
Let cream cheese reach room temperature to soften.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Add taco seasoning and mix well.
Pour mixture into the chilled pie plate.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Just before serving, top dip mixture with shredded lettuce, beef, onions, tomatoes and cheeses, layering each.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: date swirl cookies
directions: Combine dates, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/3 cup water in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until pasty, about 2 minutes.
Add chopped nuts.
Let cool.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together shortening and brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in with dry ingredients.
Toss dough on lightly floured board.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick (can divide and make 2 rolls).
Spread date mixture over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll and wrap in wax paper. Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Cut in slices.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and wild rice chowder
directions: Cook vegies in chicken stock until soft (keep covered to reduce evaporation of broth).
Add cooked rice.
Add water and cornstarch (premixed).
Add other ingredients and heat.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion. Shape into small balls.
Blend soup and water.
Heat in pressure pan until mixture begins to simmer. Add meat balls.
Cook at 15 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.
Let pressure go down normally.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: aunt linda's baked beans
directions: Place all ingredients into baking dish or bean pot.
Bake in a slow oven, 250° to 300°, for 1 to 3 hours.
The longer baked, the better.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain on towels.
Set aside.
Combine sausage with other ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: blueberry pecan crunch
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over pan. Add layer of berries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle dry whole cake mix on top of berries and drizzle melted margarine over dry cake mix.
Top it with pecans.
For crunchy glaze, sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup sugar over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. After baking for 25 minutes, cut into pie with spoon so juices will come up.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix pumpkin pie mix, eggs and evaporated milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Melt butter and pour over top of crumbled cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix spaghetti, dressing and seasoning.
Add vegetables and mix.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain grease; add all other ingredients and warm through.
Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: goober cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and peanut butter, then add sugar.
Sift and measure flour.
Add soda, baking powder and salt.
Sift together 3 more times.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Form into walnut size balls.
Pat out with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookie pizza
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy beer dip
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand or mixer.
Pour into hollowed out bread loaf.
Cut up bread into cubes to use for dipping.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pack in lightly buttered loaf pan (a bread pan is a good size).
Bake in 350° oven about one hour, until the top is lightly browned.
Unmold and serve with Quick Cream Sauce.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased spring-form pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 325° oven.
Let stand in oven 2 hours longer with heat off.
Cake will develop crack on top characteristic of New York Cheese Cake.
Take off sides of spring-form pan and refrigerate.
Tastes better if made day before served.

title: yummy bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/4 cup evaporated milk in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth; set aside.

title: the original mississippi mud cake direct from mississippi
directions: Combine all ingredients mixing well.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes in greased long pan.
When taken from hot oven, spread with one jar of marshmallow cream on the top.
Cool and ice in pan.

title: fontenot stew
directions: Mix meat and oil and fry until brown; add salt.
Add flour, potatoes, onion and pepper.
Cook 10 more minutes; add water and cook 20 more minutes.
Serve hot over rice.

title: lazy day salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the fruit cocktail, oranges, pineapple with juice and pudding mixes.
Fold in large carton of whipped topping and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: coconut custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour into individual ovenproof baking cups or into 1 small casserole dish.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: strawberry apple cider
directions: Combine in large coffee pot.
Stir until Jell-o is dissolved. Heat to serve.

title: baked savory pork chops
directions: In a deep baking dish, place chops and sprinkle with salt and pepper on each chop. Place a slice of lemon and 1 tsp of brown sugar. Mix the other ingredients together and pour around the chops until they are covered. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour, or until done.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Cook until thick.
Use egg whites as a meringue or beat and fold into cooked mixture.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
In medium mixing bowl, blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely. Cut into squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place 10 to 12 cups popped popcorn in large bowl.
In large saucepan, place melted butter.
Keeping over flame, add marshmallows, stirring rapidly, until marshmallows melt.
Add vanilla.
Stir in popcorn until well coated and form into balls.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix 1/3 cup melted butter with crushed gingersnaps and press into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt; add softened ice cream.
Pour over gingersnap crust.
Cover and freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix milk, Kool-Aid and 1/2 of Cool Whip together until stiff. Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Add rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: melanie's cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Add flour and cornstarch.
Add milk; heat, then add broth.
Add soda, cheese, salt and pepper. Add broccoli, if desired.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Brown beef, pepper, onion and celery.
Drain and add sauce. Layer in casserole the meat, cabbage and cheese until gone.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or microwave 25 minutes; then rotate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1 cup cheese in milk and butter.
Add grated potatoes. Blend in sour cream, 1/2 cup grated cheese and seasonings.
Spread in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining grated cheese and bake 20 minutes in 250° oven.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Separately mix brown sugar with cinnamon.
Pour half of batter in pan 9 x 12-inches.
Place half of brown sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.
Swirl with knife. Pour remaining batter on top of this.
Pour remaining brown sugar and cinnamon mixture and swirl again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, wine vinegar and raspberry preserves together. Add to bowl with broccoli, sliced purple onion, cheese and raisins.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours or longer.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine lemon juice and Eagle Brand. Stir in cranberries, pineapple and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread into a 9 x 13 glass dish. Freeze. This salad is good served both frozen or thawed. You can freeze this salad in 1-cup containers and serve it as a dessert. Either way, it is good. Serves 12 or 15.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Cut and peel apples and put in pie crust.
Pour lemon juice over apples.
In separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients together. Pour over apples. Cut up the margarine and place over pie.
Then spread sour cream over pie.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, then turn down to 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: herb roasted chicken(serves four)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wash chicken; pat dry.
Cream together 3 tablespoons butter, garlic, Parmesan, sage, thyme and basil.
This mixture goes under the skin, so turn chicken breast side up and make skin as loose as possible.
Spread herb mixture underneath the skin.
Smear butter on outside of skin.
Put chicken breast up in roasting pan and place in oven.
Melt remaining butter.
Cook chicken 15 minutes, basting once.
Reduce to 350°.
Roast 20 minutes per pound, basting with butter every 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in large 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle some shredded cheese on top.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serves about 15.

title: gourmet wild rice
directions: Soak wild rice overnight.
Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Mix with rice.
Add green pepper, onion, chopped celery, sliced mushrooms and pimento.
Mix in cream of chicken and mushroom soup. Mix well; pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered.
Don't peek!

title: chocolate chip cookie mix(for chocolate chip "mix cookies")
directions: You will also need 4 one gallon freezer bags (7 cups per bag to store).

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl. Stir in rolled oats and raisins.
Beat egg and milk.
Add fat or oil; set aside.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are wet, leaving batter lumpy.

title: rahmschnitzel(veal cutlets in cream sauce)
directions: Salt and pepper meat; put flour on both sides.
Brown in oil over medium heat in large skillet.
Add parsley, mushrooms and onion.
Add a little water, cover skillet and simmer slowly 30 minutes.
(Add more water, if necessary.) Dissolve bouillon in skillet and allow to simmer another 10 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Stir cream cheese and blend all the rest of the ingredients except for walnuts and paprika together.
Spread on 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts and paprika.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easter egg salad
directions: Peel 12 hard-boiled eggs.
Soak 4 eggs in each color, then cut eggs and devil in the usual way.
Arrange frill of lettuce around tray.
Turn deviled eggs upside-down in center of lettuce ring.

title: brunch muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Paper line muffin pans.
In medium bowl, combine egg, milk and oil.
Stir in cereal.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: mackin's rice pudding
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vanilla, egg and cornstarch together in bowl. Cook rice according to package.
Add milk and raisins and bring to full boil, stirring constantly throughout, following steps. Lower heat and cook for 10 minutes.
Add bowl of remaining ingredients.
Bring to full boil again.
Stir for 10 minutes. Refrigerate.

title: tortilla delights
directions: Mix all ingredients (a mixer works best).
Spread evenly on flour tortillas, rolling each tortilla tightly.
Refrigerate rolled tortillas in a single layer for 4 hours or longer, then slice into rounds about 1/3 inch wide.

title: baby cheese cakes
directions: With a mixer, mix cheese, sugar, vanilla, and eggs. Place wafer in the bottom of cupcake paper, in a cupcake pan. Pour cheese mixture on top of wafers 1/2 full.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Pour combined barbecue sauce and dressing over chicken. Cover, marinate 1 hour.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place chicken on greased rack of broiler pan or greased grill.
Broil or grill, uncovered, over low coals, 10 minutes on each side or until tender, brushing occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spice tea
directions: In a percolator or in a pan on the stove eye, mix pineapple juice, cranberry juice and water.
If you are using a percolator, in the basket, mix the brown sugar, cloves and stick cinnamon.
If you are using a pan on the stove, mix the brown sugar, cloves and stick of cinnamon with the juices and bring to a slow boil.
Serve while the mixture is hot.
Makes 10 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil in a large bowl; beat well. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add to sugar mixture. Beat well. Stir in carrots, pecans, pineapple and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and allow to cool completely.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Peel top third of each.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Combine
raisins,	pecans and
cinnamon.
Fill cavities of	apples	with
mixture.	Pour
maple
syrup
over apples.
Top each
with 1 tablespoon butter.
Pour water into bottom of	dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 2.

title: zucchini bread(the best ever!)
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended except raisins, nuts and zucchini.
Add these ingredients and blend well.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Divide batter between the 2 pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and continue cooling on a rack. Freezes well and makes great gifts!

title: burritos
directions: Fry hamburger and onion, drain off grease.
Add green chiles and taco seasoning mix.
Cook according to package directions. Add Cheddar cheese soup; mix well.
Place in center of heated tortillas, sprinkle shredded cheese on top and wrap.

title: hot crab cocktail spread
directions: Thoroughly combine cream cheese with milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain and flake crab and add to cream cheese mixture along with the green onion.
Put into a greased 8-inch pie plate or small shallow baking dish.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until heated all the way through. Keep cocktail spread warm over a candle warmer.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, set aside.
Lay crescent rolls on a cookie sheet flat like a pie dough and bake at 350 F until brown.
Mix nest 4 ingredients together, set aside.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/3 cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook brown rice according to package directions.
Combine cooked rice, bell pepper, onion and celery.
Make dressing with 1 teaspoon curry, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in salad.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: crescent roll meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all ingredients except rolls and cheese (shredded).
Tear rolls into two equal halves.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet overlapping the edges.
Press the edges to seal so that the whole cookie sheet is covered by dough.
Spoon 2/3 of meat mixture in center of dough.
Pull dough over top to meet in the middle and seal.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Take out; spread rest of meat on top and sprinkle cheese. Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In Pyrex dish, layer noodles, soup, tuna and celery.
Put butter on top.
Cook until thickens.

title: hershey pie
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows over low heat until smooth and creamy.
Break up candy bars in small pieces; melt in milk.
Let cool.
Whip cream and fold into chocolate mixture with vanilla. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: brunch braid
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter. Add green onions and red pepper. Cook, stirring, until vegetables are tender. Beat 6 eggs with milk, salt and basil. Stir in ham. Pour egg mixture over vegetables. Scramble until eggs are thickened but still moist. Remove from heat; set aside. In a medium bowl, toss together broccoli, Swiss cheese and lemon juice. Set aside. Unroll refrigerated pizza crust onto a greased baking sheet. Pat dough to form a 14 x 9-inch rectangle. Spread reserved egg mixture in a 3-inch wide strip lengthwise down center of dough. Top with reserved broccoli mixture. Make cuts in dough at 1-inch intervals on both sides of rectangle, just to edge of filling. Fold dough strips diagonally over filling, overlapping strips and alternating from side to side to give a braided appearance. In a small bowl, beat together remaining egg and 1 tablespoon water. Brush top of dough with egg mixture. Sprinkle with poppy seeds. Bake in preheated 375° oven until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Slice to serve. Yield: 6 servings.

title: italian beans parmesan(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter in a large pan or spray pan with oil.
Saute onion and pepper until soft.
Add potatoes and saute for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook over high heat until slightly thickened.
Add beans and heat through.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat 2 egg whites until fluffy.
Slowly add sugar and cinnamon.
Beat until stiff.
Add whiskey.
Fold in nuts.

title: grandmother's cheese dip
directions: Remove stems and seeds from peppers.
Finely chop onion. Blend onion and peppers in blender with a small amount of mayonnaise.
Then put everything into a mixer and mix until creamy.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Best made several days before using to let ingredients blend.

title: sweet and sour cole slaw
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and toss thoroughly to mix.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Stir well.

title: pineapple coconut sheet cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in an oblong pan.
Mix pudding as directed.
Pour over cake while warm.
Mix sugar and pineapple juice until all sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Let cool until cold.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken.
Pick from bone.
Cut in pieces in casserole dish.
Put broth and soup in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Melt margarine.
Mix with flour and milk.
Pour on chicken and bake at 350° until brown.

title: grandma's molasses cake
directions: Grease pan.
Combine milk, eggs, molasses and butter.
Beat well, then add cinnamon and flour.
Bake in a big bread pan (9 x 13-inch) on a old wood stove (for a large family) in 350° oven. Check after 30 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
If it comes out clean, cake is done.
Makes 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: maple-apple crisp
directions: Core apples and cut into slices about 3/4-inch thick at widest part.
Toss in bowl with lemon juice to prevent browning.
Place apples in a lightly buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle syrup evenly over the apples.
In a small bowl, combine flour, salt and sugar and cut in butter as if making a pie crust.
Distribute mixture evenly over apples.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes or until juices are bubbling and topping is crisp.
Serve hot, warm or room temperature with vanilla or coffee ice cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and 1 stick melted butter and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks of margarine for 15 minutes.
Spread this mixture over graham crackers; slice 4 bananas over this.
Cover with 1 large can crushed pineapple (drained), 1 large Cool Whip, cherries and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar and milk.
In bottom of pie crusts, add 1/2 of cream cheese mixture.
Put nuts on top of cheese mixture, then Cool Whip and cherry pie filling on top.

title: rice and cherries in the snow
directions: Cook rice in water 15 minutes.
Add salt, sugar, butter and 3 cups of milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Using the 1/3 cup of milk, soften gelatin.
Cook rice until mixture thickens slightly.
Add softened gelatin, cook 1 minute. Remove from heat and add almond extract.
Cool.
When cool, fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.
Put cherry pie filling on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and fold in cream.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon.
Add onion and cook until tender; drain.
Stir in soup, salt and paprika.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through but do not boil.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream, then strawberries and bananas.

title: american apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Rub in butter, then mix in cheese.
Add sufficient milk to make a soft but not sticky dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead dough lightly.
Pat out dough in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Peel and core apples; slice thinly.
Arrange in rows across dough. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon mixed together.
Brush over with melted butter.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 425° oven.
Best eaten fresh.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, saute onions, jalapeno pepper and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, green chili tomatoes, tomato soup, beef bouillon, chicken broth and water.
Stir in red chilies and cilantro.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer about 1 hour. Serve in bowls with tortillas and cheese at side for everyone to use desired amounts on top of soup.

title: echo
directions: Break up the ground beef in a medium size skillet.
Heat and cover meat on a stove.
As the ground beef begins to brown, throw in onions and any desired seasoning, then stir to mix onions and beef.
Once beef is brown, drain grease.
Add the eggs which have been stirred in a bowl (similar to scrambled eggs prep). Pour the eggs over the beef and onion and let set until eggs are cooked.
Add seasoning as desired.
Once eggs are cooked, layer the cheese on top.
Once cheese is melted, serve and enjoy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef into small bits. Mix approximately 2/3 of the beef with the other ingredients. Mix thoroughly and shape into ball. Roll ball in rest of beef. Serve with bacon-flavored crackers.

title: oven kalua pig
directions: You will need foil.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Stir together.
Cut in shortening. Mix in cream of chicken soup.
Bring together into a ball.
On a floured surface, roll out dumplings and cut into strips.
Drop into slow rolling boil of chicken broth with chicken meat.
Cook until done.

title: grandma drake's sweet dill pickles
directions: Fill sterilized jars with sliced cucumbers (I slice mine in sticks).
Add a piece of dill.
Cover with boiling syrup.
Seal. Process in water bath for 15 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix 3 cups sugar and flour, then add milk; mix well.
Add margarine.
(I cook this in an 8 or 9-inch iron skillet.)
Let this come to a boil.
Put the 1/4 cup sugar in another small skillet. Be careful browning this sugar.
When it is brown, take the other skillet off the heat, add the browned sugar and cook until a soft ball forms in a cup of cold water.

title: italian beef
directions: Fill crock pot 3/4 full of water.
Cook 8 hours on high.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 8 minutes.
Add tea; chill. Add fruit juices and pineapple.
Mellow in refrigerator 2 hours. Add 2 quarts ginger ale and ice just before serving.
Serves 50.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water.
Carrots should be firm.
Mix with other ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sugar, sour cream and margarine.
Crush Heath Bars and add to cake.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: batter for deep fried butterfly shrimp
directions: Combine flour and salt; make a well in center.
Add egg and water.
Stir batter until smooth and let stand, covered, for 3 hours.

title: pan fries
directions: Wash potatoes and slice (with skins left on).
Slice onions into rings.
In large skillet, pour oil.
Let it heat to almost boiling and add potatoes and onions.
Season with salt and pepper and other seasonings to taste.
Cook, covered, for about 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook until light brown.
Fork will stick through potatoes easily when done.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground hamburger in a Corning Ware casserole on top of the stove or in the microwave.
Return casserole to crock-pot, heating the base.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: shoyu chicken #1
directions: Marinate whole chicken in all of the ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer with cover on pot, 25 to 30 minutes or until tender. Turn chicken over once while simmering to brown evenly. Cool, then chop into small pieces and arrange on platter.
Top with Chinese parsley and chopped green onions, if desired.

title: 2 large loaves bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in very warm water, 1 teaspoon flour and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Wait 5 minutes.
Make a well in the 12 cups of flour.
Pour in yeast mixture with some flour for a soft dough. Add 4 cups hot water.
Work dough with hand.
Cover and let rise to double in size, 1 to 2 hours.
Punch down dough and knead 8 minutes.
Let rise until double in size again.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Brush with hot water just before it comes out of the oven.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add chicken pieces, green pepper and onion.
Put in as much garlic and salt and pepper as you like. (Just according to your taste.)
Cook ingredients until chicken turns white.
Add as much Worcestershire sauce as you like.
Cook until chicken is done, about 15 minutes.

title: fluffy rice and chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture, the rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and half the onion soup mix.

title: monsters (candy)
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler; mix in noodles and peanuts. Spoon on cookie sheet lined with wax paper to harden.
I put them in the refrigerator because it only takes a short while to harden. Enjoy.

title: u-name it
directions: Mix lemon or orange Jell-O, drained pineapple juice plus 1 cup pineapple juice, adding boiling water to make 2 cups liquid.
When this starts to congeal, add marshmallows, drained pineapple, cream cheese and mayonnaise (which have been creamed together).
Whip and add whipping cream.
In separate bowl, add 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup cold water to red Jell-O.
When it has set, put above mixture on top.
Do the same with green Jell-O and put on top of lemon or orange layer.

title: baked onions
directions: Place onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add 1 cup of cold water.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Remove onions from oven and cut off the top and bottom.
Squeeze the onion and the delicious part will pop out.
Throw away the skin.
Season the onion with salt and margarine.
Will serve 4 to 6 people.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, gently mix together cranberry sauce and apple chunks with their juices until combined.
Take care not to mash apples.
In another bowl, mix the sour cream with the lemon juice and sugar.

Stir into the cranberry mixture, blending well. Pour fruit mixture into a foil-lined 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Cover and freeze salad at least 4 hours or until ready to serve. Remove from pan onto serving platter.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and add grated cheese and cream-style corn.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan layer cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside.
Cream together butter, shortening and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy, using electric mixer at medium speed.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Blend in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition, using electric mixer at low speed.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Beat egg whites in another bowl until stiff peaks form, using electric mixer at high speed.
Fold into cake batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and waxed paper-lined 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven 25 minutes or until cake tester or wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on racks.
Spread the top of one layer with Creamy Pecan Frosting.
Place second layer on top. Spread with frosting.
Top with third layer.
Frost sides and top of cake with frosting.
Makes 12 servings.

title: old fashioned butterscotch pie
directions: Put white sugar in an iron skillet over medium heat, stirring until it melts, to make a syrup.
Gently add boiling water and let simmer.
In a saucepan, mix milk, cornstarch, egg yolks and brown sugar; cooking until thick.
Add the caramelized sugar and let cook until mixture thickens again.
Add flavorings and butter. Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites and water until stiff, adding tablespoon of sugar.
Put meringue on pie and brown in 400° oven, about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate butterscotch brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. Arrange single layer of saltine crackers on each sheet.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and boil for one minute.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over each sheet of saltines and spread to cover all saltines. Cook in oven for 5 minutes or until bubbling.
Remove from oven and immediately pour one 12 ounce package of morsels over each sheet and spread quickly.
If chips do not melt, place back in oven.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate sheets until hard. Remove brittle from cookie sheet.
Peel off foil.
Break into pieces by hand.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: college fudge squares
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add cocoa and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and salt alternating with milk. Fold in nuts.
Grease and flour a 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Frost with chocolate icing.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine noodles with oil.
Spread about 1/2 cup sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
Make a layer each of noodles, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, tomato-meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat twice.
Bake 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: ham pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except biscuits, in baking dish.
Cover and cook at 350° until heated through, approximately 30 minutes. Remove from oven and top with biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, until biscuits are brown.

title: forgotten dessert
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and beat for 10 minutes on medium speed.
Spread in 9 x 15-inch pan (ungreased). Place in oven.
Turn off heat.
Leave oven closed overnight. Spread with sweetened whipped cream or Cool Whip topping.
Top with sliced strawberries or other fruit.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apples and cranberries.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
Mix together.
Need 8 x 9-inch pan.
Add 2 tablespoons water.

title: crabmeat deluxe
directions: Place the cream cheese on a small serving dish.
Drain the crabmeat and mix in the cocktail sauce and lemon juice.
Pour the crabmeat over the cream cheese and garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy chocolate kisses
directions: You will need double boiler, small spoon, large spoon, cookie sheet and waxed paper.

title: honey cake
directions: Bring honey to a boil.
Cool.
Cream margarine and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat until light and fluffy.
Add honey.
Combine flour with dry ingredients, then add to honey mixture alternately with sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Spoon in buttered cake pan or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Before end of baking, lower baking temperature to 300° to prevent burning.
When cake tests done, remove from oven.
Remove from pan and cool on cake rack.

title: pumpkin oat streusel muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line twelve muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, oats, sugar, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda, and salt.
Add nuts (if desired).
Mix well.
In medium bowl, combine pumpkin, milk, oil and egg; blend well.
Add to dry ingredients all at once; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened (do not overmix).
Fill muffin cups almost full. Sprinkle with streusel, patting gently.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool muffins in pan on wire rack 5 minutes. Remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: zippy glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in brown sugar, mustard and salt. Add cooked carrots.
Heat, stirring constantly, until carrots are nicely glazed, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown meat in butter and add seasonings and onions.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, sour cream and cottage cheese.
In baking dish, arrange layers on noodles and meat mixture.
Begin and end with noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a small square dish, layer avocado dip, sour cream, chopped onions and picante sauce.
Sprinkle cheese heavily onto layer. Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with chips.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb in water.
Remove from heat.
Add jello, sugar, pineapple and nuts.
Chill.

title: italian new york cheesecake
directions: Blend Ricotta and cream cheese with the sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter and mix well.
Fold in sour cream, then mix on low speed until blended.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Place in cold oven and turn heat to 325°.
Bake 1 hour.
Do not open oven.
Turn oven off after 1 hour and keep in oven for 2 hours longer.
Do not open oven!

title: apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Serve with chopped nuts on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cut apples in wedges.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Mix together and press into pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: chocolate pecan squares
directions: Mix brown sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all
ingredients
in mixing bowl.
Knead on floured surface.
Cut out biscuits and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: praline peach cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and water.
Stir until smooth.
Add peaches.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: jello salad
directions: Use sheet cake pan.
Add marshmallows to jello and hot water so they will melt.
When almost set, add 1 cup crushed pineapple. Add sliced bananas.
When set, spread on topping.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions on back of box. Brown ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add garlic, garlic salt, finely chopped onion, chopped sweet basil, tomato paste, 4 cans water and a pinch of chili powder.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: pickled onions
directions: Sprinkle onions with salt; add water to cover. Let stand 12 hours in a cool place. Drain and rinse. Combine sugar, mustard seed, horseradish and vinegar. Simmer 15 minutes. Pack onions in a large mouth quart jar or plastic bowl with lid. Add hot peppers. Pour liquid over onions. Cover and refrigerate when cool.

title: wonderful cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; chop dried beef.
Mix together all ingredients.
Mold into 2 cheese balls.

title: pear bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients along with yogurt or buttermilk.
Fold in chopped pears.
Pour in small or large pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: persimmon nut cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add oil and butter.
Continue beating.
Sift together and stir in dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add persimmon pulp and mix well.
Pour half into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Mix 1 cup nuts (finely ground), 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 4 tablespoons brown sugar.
Mix and sprinkle over the butter in the pan.
Add remaining batter and bake at 300° for 60 minutes or bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: marinated scroodle and noodle salad
directions: Marinate all but noodles overnight.
Boil noodles; add to marinated mixture.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until smooth and spreadable.
Separate the slices of ham and turkey, laying one slice of turkey on each slice of ham and then spread with cheese mixture.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks. Chill.
Just before serving, slice into 1/2-inch slices.

title: chili dip
directions: In saucepan, add chili and cut cheese into small pieces.
Heat until all cheese is melted.
Serve with Tostitos.
Best hot!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, bread cubes, nuts, onion and cheese in large bowl.
Mix Miracle Whip, lemon juice and salt together.
Add to chicken mixture and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick and creamy cheese potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Boil or bake until tender.
Mix evaporated milk, dry minced onion and grated cheese together over low heat until cheese melts.
Set aside.
Lightly grease a heavy skillet. Slice cooked potatoes and arrange in layers in skillet.
Alternate each layer with a layer of the cheese sauce (ending with the cheese sauce).
Cover and cook over low heat until potatoes are heated through, or layer in greased 2-quart casserole and microwave on High 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chop onion and bell pepper; place on top of chicken.
Pour both cans of Ro-Tel tomatoes over chicken.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: melting moments
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cornstarch.
Blend in butter until soft dough is formed.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in coconut.
Place on ungreased baking sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first ingredients.
Pour into a baking pan.
Mix flour, Crisco and milk.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake at 350° until crust is lightly brown.

title: grama muir's chocolate cake(1926)
directions: Beat eggs, salt, butter and sugar to a cream.
Then add dry cocoa, sour milk and flour to the mixture.
To this, add 1 cup boiling water with soda and beat 5 minutes.
Grease and flour an 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Blend peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Mix the milk, 2 cups sugar and flour.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add the cream, eggs, vanilla and peaches.
Mix together. Add enough milk to make 1 gallon.
Freeze.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and spread thickly and to the edges.
Roll up tortillas.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
They will keep for days.
To serve, cut into 1-inch pieces and serve with your favorite salsa or picante sauce.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all of the preceding ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts in the bottom of pan.
Cut each biscuit into fourths and put them into the pan to make a single layer.
Heat all remaining ingredients and pour over nuts and biscuits.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until biscuits start to be light brown.
Invert over and onto a large tray immediately. Cool slightly.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken into strips and cook in frying pan.
Set chicken aside.
Cook vegetables in 1/4 cup oil until soft.
Drain vegetables.
Add water and fajita mix to vegetables.
Mix well. Add cooked chicken.
Cook until mixture is mixed together well and hot.
Put mixture onto warmed tortillas.
Serves 6 people 2 each.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries in bottom of pan, then drain pineapple.
Pour on top of the cherries and pineapple.
Melt 2 sticks butter; pour on, then add coconut and pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pineapple. Add pineapple. Drop 1 teaspoon at a time into deep hot fat. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: lentil soup
directions: Put bone, lentils and stock in deep pot.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once or twice during baking.
Great with Easy Chicken Breasts!
Can be cooked at same time and temperature.

title: mini pizza(microwave)
directions: First, you get the muffins out and put sauce on them.
Then you go and put the cheese on them.
Then you microwave them.
You will have a good pizza.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Mix in beans, salsa and season pack and top with cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together.
Add milk, baking powder, vanilla and flour (add more flour accordingly for texture).
Roll dough to 1/8 to 3/16-inch thick and cut.
Place on cookie sheet, allowing space for spreading and rising.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or ice when baked.
Bake in oven at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Best cookies ever.
I usually double recipe to make about 6 dozen cookies.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: *Soak raisins in hot water to cover for 30 minutes; drain thoroughly.

title: chocolate clouds
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar and vanilla, beating until stiff.
Sift cocoa onto egg white mixture folding gently until just combined.
Fold in chocolate bits.
Place parchment paper on cookie sheets and drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls onto paper.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes or just until dry.
Cool on wire rack.

title: alice's poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, undiluted soup, sour cream and water chestnuts. Place in greased casserole dish.
Mix together crushed crackers and margarine.
Put over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed over this.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: english trifle with american ingredients!
directions: In large glass bowl, put sponge cake.
Spread jam, layer of fruit cocktail (or any canned fruit) and layer of vanilla pudding. Let stand until set.
Add a layer of cream.
Decorate with sprinkles or fresh fruit.
Refrigerate until serving. `This recipe can also be used in individual dessert bowls.
An alternative would be to pour jello over the sponge or cream sherry and let set, then add the other layer.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper in skillet; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Combine 1/2 cup of cheese, sour cream and egg together.
Remove meat mixture from heat and stir in sour cream mixture; mix well.
If too thick, add a small amount of water.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 325° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: brad's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Set aside 1 cup cake mix.
Mix remainder of cake mix, 1 egg and 2 tablespoons of oil and press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for the crust.

title: margaritas
directions: In blender, pour in all ingredients.
Add ice to 2-inches from top.
(Do not overfill.)
Blend on high 1 minute and serve.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler or in a pan with hot water. (Do not let water boil.)
Add sugar, coffee and egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir until mixture has thickened.
Remove from heat.
Let cool.
Whip cream.
Add slightly cooled chocolate mixture.
Spoon mousse into individual serving dishes.
Let cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Garnish each serving with a spoonful of whipped cream.

title: roll your own soft tacos
directions: Cook or prepare each ingredient separately and place in serving dish.
Everyone makes their own soft tacos to their liking with all or part of the ingredients.
Ole!
If company's coming, I make a pot of pinto beans and Spanish rice.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown beef in lard or drippings.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Pour off drippings.
Cook vegetables in water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine vegetables, soup, salt, pepper, soy sauce and celery and stir into meat mixture.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover, sprinkle with Chinese noodles and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple together.
Add sour cream, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix until blended.
Pour into a container.

title: cookie spread
directions: Mix ingredients together, except cookies.
Spread mixture on chocolate cookies.
Chill until firm.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add the graham cracker crumbs; mix well.
Press into pan to form crust.

title: top-of-the-morning pancakes
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together muffin mix, cereal and spice.
In a small mixing bowl combine eggs and milk; add all at once to muffin mixture, stirring until blended but still slightly lumpy.

Pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot well-greased griddle. Cook over medium heat, 1 to 2 minutes per side or until golden brown, turning to cook other side when pancakes have a bubbly surface and slightly dry edge.
Serve with margarine or butter and syrup.
Makes eight 4-inch pancakes.

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pastry shell.
Add almond extract to cherry pie filling and carefully spoon over cheese layer.
Chill until set.
Substitute blueberry pie filling sometimes.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in a bowl.
In saucepan, put margarine, cocoa and cold water. Bring to a boil. Pour boiling mixture over sugar and flour. Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla. Bake 25 minutes at 400° in an 11 x 16-inch pan.
Make icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows in heavy saucepan. Add rest of ingredients and mix well, while marshmallows are warm. Spoon mixture onto piece of foil and shape into cake shape. Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and place in buttered casserole.
Spread with topping.

title: easy hollandaise salad
directions: With eggbeater or electric mixer, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored; add salt and cayenne pepper.
Add 1/4 cup melted butter (about 1 teaspoon at a time), beating constantly.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup melted butter with lemon juice.
Slowly add, about 2 teaspoons at a time, to yolk mixture, beating constantly. Serve over broccoli, hot asparagus, broiled fish, etc.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Heat and cook over medium heat until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat; cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt and peanut butter; mix.
Add oatmeal; stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: three day coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) layers.
Split both layers; cool.
Blend sugar, sour cream and coconut together.
Chill.
Spread all but 1 cup between the layers.
Blend remaining cup with Cool Whip and spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and make into balls.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients; add eggs and vanilla.
Add (after sifting) the next 3 ingredients.
