Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crescent roll cheeseburgers
directions: Brown hamburger with barbecue sauce; drain.
Pat out one can of rolls on cookie sheet.
Put hamburger on rolls; place cheese on top of hamburger.
Put other can of rolls on top; pinch sides together.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes until rolls are golden brown. Slice and serve.

title: orange sweet potato casserole
directions: Process sweet potatoes, 2 tablespoons butter, 4 tablespoons brown sugar, rum and salt.
Fold in 1/2 of oranges.
Spread in 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining oranges and whole nuts in decorative pattern.
Combine remaining sugar, butter and chopped pecans.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: outrageous cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 baking pan.
Sprinkle on graham cracker crumbs and mix well.
Press onto bottom of pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Sprinkle with chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts.
Press down firmly on mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely before serving in the pan.
Makes 2 - 3 dozen bars.

title: lasagna-style casserole
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain.
Fry meat until browned; drain off fat.
Add pizza sauce, onion and basil to meat and mix well. In a bowl, combine egg and cottage cheese or Ricotta.
In a greased 12 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of the pasta. Spoon cheese mixture over pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Layer remaining pasta, meat and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, covered, at 425° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 to 8 minutes longer or until heated through.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in oil.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil. Put in 2 handfuls of noodles.
Cook 3 minutes uncovered.

title: yogurt dressing
directions: Stir mustard, salt and white pepper to taste.
Add lemon juice; stir well to dissolve.
Blend all ingredients.
Mix in yogurt until thoroughly incorporated, then vigorously stir in oil. Sprinkle parsley over top.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend
sugar
into softened cream cheese.
Mix together drained
pineapple,
strawberries with juice, bananas, chopped nuts
and Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures and pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Keep leftovers frozen.
Delicious.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix butter and sugar in top of double boiler; add milk and chocolate.
Cook over hot water for 30 minutes.
Do not stir while cooking.
Remove from heat and beat.
You may store in refrigerator and reheat as needed.
If you wish to have a thinner sauce, add cream, but do not add water.

title: beef and cabbage over rice
directions: In a large, nonstick skillet, brown ground beef and onion over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, breaking meat into 3/4-inch pieces.
Pour off drippings.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes, ketchup and sugar.
Add cole slaw, mixing well, and cook for 5 minutes or until cole slaw is crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bing cherry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot juice.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Let cool some, then add cherries and nuts.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and beat again.
Beat in margarine, then vanilla.
Add flour and beat well.
Then add pecans.
Pour into two greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: granola
directions: Mix the peanut butter and honey in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring well every 15 minutes.
Store in covered container.

title: zucchini mousaka
directions: In vegetable oil, cook zucchini and sliced onion until tender. Place in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
In the same skillet, brown the ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce. Add minced garlic, salt and cinnamon and mix.
Pour meat mixture over zucchini.

title: volcano dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in slow cooker.
Brown ground chuck; drain fat.
Add ground chuck to Velveeta cheese.
Add 2 cans Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix well.
After cheese melts, completely simmer at least 30 minutes.
Serve over Fritos or tortilla chips or favorite chips.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Melt cheese with Ro-Tel. Squeeze the spinach and add to the cheese mix. Serve hot with chips.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Mix cream cheese and soup.
Then add hamburger and broccoli; mix well.
Line baking dish with 1 1/2 cans of crescent rolls.
Pour hamburger mixture in baking dish. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cut the remaining 1/2 can of crescent rolls into strips, about 1-inch wide.
Put on top to make crisscross topped pie.
Bake according to crescent roll directions or until golden brown.

title: norm's meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Top with ketchup before baking.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain and add rest of the ingredients to pan.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered.
Sprinkle with Chinese noodles and bake 2 to 5 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth if you have it.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Saute onion and celery in margarine. Add cheese and melt.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: aunt mae's "chicken dressing" or ham bone
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good.
Take broth from chicken or meat bone.
Make up like making corn bread.
Put in a 400° oven; bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Separate eggs.
Add yolks, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil. Stir constantly.
Remove from stove and add vanilla and egg whites.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: farina spoon bread
directions: Scald milk in top part of double boiler.
Slowly stir in farina and cook over boiling water until thickened.
Add salt, baking powder, beaten egg yolks and shortening.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish and bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and water until frothy, but not stiff.
Add pecans and mix well until all nuts are coated.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Add to nuts and mix thoroughly. Place in buttered shallow pan, about 10 x 15-inch.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on aluminum foil to cool.
Separate with spoon if nuts are too clustered.

title: easy pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine oat bran, sugar and baking powder in food processor with large metal blade.
Allow the food processor to grind the oat bran as you combine the moist ingredients in a separate bowl or blender.
Add whole cranberries to the oat bran in the food processor; pulse the mixture for a few seconds to break up the berries.
Combine all ingredients, including chopped walnuts, in a large bowl; mix gently.
Pour batter into muffin pans lined with paper baking cups.
Bake 17 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick; it should come out moist but not wet.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cukes, onions and salt in large pan.
Add ice.
Stir well; let set 3 hours.
Drain and pick ice out.
Put in kettle and add other ingredients.
Boil until cukes turn color.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Heat a large, heavy skillet and then add the chicken strips (no additional oil needed), green pepper and onion.
Stir-fry until chicken is lightly browned and veggies are crisp-tender.
(I sometimes cook the chicken and veggies separately.)

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mixture will be soft.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Place meatballs in a single layer on waxed paper-lined cookie sheets.
Freeze until solid.
Store in freezer bags until ready to cook.

title: punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water to make simple syrup.
Pour in jar and refrigerate.
Add the cranberry juice, lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice, ginger ale and the simple syrup.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together the first five ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture with liquid, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl the juice, cream of coconut and Sprite. Place ice cream on top.
Stir and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1/2 bottle of ginger ale to each bowl of punch when ready to serve.

title: yogurt-relish dip
directions: In mixing bowl combine yogurt, relish and spices.
Cover. Chill before serving.
Serve with Fruit Dunkers.

title: can't fail custard pie
directions: Put all the ingredients into a blender and blend for 20 seconds.
Pour into a buttered 9 to 10-inch pie plate (need lip on plate).
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg, water, vanilla, almond extract and peanut butter and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix crab meat, chopped onions, chopped celery, herb stuffing, mayonnaise and half and half.
Sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Drain.
Put it and remainder of ingredients into soup pot.
Simmer 1 hour or more. Excellent with cornbread!

title: heavenly cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add juices.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in pineapple, shredded cheese and whipped cream.
Pour into mold.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add Kool-Aid and sugar. Mix well.
Add cold water and freeze for 24 hours.
Let thaw 2 hours before serving.
Mash with a potato masher or knife.
Serve.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: spaghetti ala'more
directions: Brown ground beef until cooked; drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in a little oil; drain.
Mix together with soup, water and 1/2 cup cheese and blend into cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup grated Cheddar.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: grandma's sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices.
Lay evenly in a 10 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Spread sugar, flour, cinnamon and flavoring over top.
Add water; shake pan to blend ingredients.

title: hot ham buns
directions: Mix margarine, mustard and onion.
Spread on hamburger buns. Put 1 slice of ham and a slice of Swiss cheese on each bun.
Wrap each bun in tinfoil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Combine all ingredients except rolls and butter in bowl; mix well.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles, press to seal edges. Spoon about 1/4 cup mixture into each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners to top.
Twist slightly to seal.
Brush with melted butter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned. Makes 4 servings.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth ball on board dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter, place on greased sheet and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Grease baking pan with some butter or margarine.
Heat butter, marshmallows, dry milk and milk mix in saucepan over low heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and coconut until coated.
Empty into the buttered pan. Rub a little butter on the back of the spoon and use it to pat the mixture evenly in the pan.
Cool.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: broccoli & cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all in a bowl and add dressing.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 24 x 18-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil in baking pan.
Place steak on foil.
Mix soup and soup mix; spread on steak.
Top steak with vegetables.
Sprinkle water on vegetables.
Fold foil over and seal securely.
Bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, put flour; cut in butter.
Add sugar.
Beat egg, vinegar and water; add to flour and butter.
Form into a ball. Will make 3 pie crusts.

title: dock jim(korean steamed chicken)
directions: Cook chicken in water, salt and chili pepper in pressure cooker, 25 minutes at 10 pounds.
Drain meat; reserve broth.
Cut meat from bones; reserve.
Reheat broth.
Mix soy sauce and flour; stir into boiling broth until thickened.
Add chicken, scallions, garlic and seeds.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Mix in egg. Add dry ingredients and mix. Stir in nuts, apples, water and vanilla. Bake in greased 9-inch pie pan or 1-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve slightly warm with whipped cream.

title: corned beef loaf
directions: Grind corned beef.
Beat eggs.
Combine corned beef, eggs and bread crumbs which have been soaked in milk a few minutes. Place in lightly sprayed (Pam) dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In blender, combine marshmallows, chocolate chips, eggs, coffee, liquor and scalded milk.
Blend at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into dessert cups or dishes.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: vegetables and biscuits
directions: In a large baking dish, pour in beef stew.
Take Bisquick and add enough water to make it a little stiff, but yet pourable; pour over beef stew.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut pie
directions: Blend milk into peanut butter in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Blend whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle chopped peanuts on top.
Chill 3 hours.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cook cake per box in 9 x 13 pan.
Take out of oven when done and poke holes in the cake.
Top with caramel sauce and sweetened condensed milk.
Then top with 1/2 bag Heath bar chips (while cake is still warm).
Cover when cool and put in refrigerator.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: seaman's pie
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Add tuna, onion and eggs.
Blend Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over tuna mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: party pizza
directions: Fry sausage until crumbly and drain well.
Melt Velveeta cheese in sausage.
Add catsup, A.1. sauce, garlic salt and oregano and blend well.
Spread on bread.
Spoon on pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Freeze on cookie sheets and store in freezer in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, bake for 10 minutes in a 450° oven directly from freezer.

title: slushy party punch
directions: Mix all the other ingredients, except ginger ale or 7-Up, with the dissolved Jell-O.
Freeze in milk cartons.
Take out of freezer 2 to 3 hours before serving.
The time will depend on how large the containers are that you poured the punch in.
This will not be completely thawed, but very icy.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale or 7-Up.
This makes 2 1/2 gallons of punch.
You can vary the flavors of Jell-O and Kool-Aid to your own needs.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream the butter in a large mixing bowl at high speed of mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
On low speed, gradually add flour, then sugar, mixing until well blended. By hand, stir in frosting mix and walnuts.
Blend well. Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes. Cool 2 hours. Remove from pan. Cool completely before serving.

title: berries and cream pie
directions: Place berries into pie crust.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over berries.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes, until crust is nicely browned and filling is set.

title: lime-tomato sipper
directions: Combine bouillon granules and boiling water, stirring until granules dissolve.
Add tomato juice and next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
To serve, pour into glasses. Garnish.
Yields 4 cups.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine flour, salt and spices.
Add sugar.
Blend in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine molasses and egg yolk in bowl.
Add soda and boiling water, blend well.
Alternate filling uncooked pie shell beginning and ending with crumbs.

title: pineapple carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender, then drain. Drain liquid from pineapple tidbits. Combine pineapple juice, orange juice, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon. Cook until thickened. Add pineapple tidbits and carrots, warm. Serves 8.

title: plum torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add flour, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Spoon batter into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place plum halves, skin side up, on top of batter.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar and lemon juice. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: jean green's olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour; mix in butter.
(Work dough with hands if it seems dry.)
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive. Shape into a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°. Bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dill weed crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Cover and shake well.
Turn bowl over occasionally.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend ingredients. Roll in balls. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: pizza treats
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. In bowl mix all other ingredients. Mix in ground beef and put by spoons full on party rye bread and freeze until ready for use.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown chicken in a small amount of oil or butter.
Blanch frozen broccoli just until you can separate it.
Lightly butter a 9 x 11-inch casserole pan.
Layer broccoli, then chicken, and pour on sauce.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bohemian sisky
directions: Scald milk.
Add scalded milk to salt, sugar and butter or oleo.
When lukewarm, add yeast.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well. Let stand until light and spongy.
Add yolks, flour and vanilla. Mix well.
Let rise until double.
Roll; cut in diamond shapes. Raise.
Fry in deep fat.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: 4th of july picnic salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in a salad bowl.
Serve with Blueberry Vinaigrette.
(For recipe, check our Condiment section.)
Serves 4.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, heat sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Cool. Store, tightly covered, at room temperature.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour and then add beaten eggs. Add buttermilk and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well and pour into 2 frozen pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top before baking.

title: chitterling salad
directions: Sprinkle chitterlings with lemon juice and let stand for at least 1 hour.
Add celery, green pepper, salt, pepper and mayonnaise. Serve on beds of lettuce. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: spinach bake
directions: Slice Spam; cook spinach according to directions, but adding onion; drain.
In medium bowl, beat eggs with milk, rice and garlic salt.
Mix spinach with rice mixture.
With slotted spoon, pat half of mixture evenly into a greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Arrange meat and cheese over spinach mixture.
Spread remaining mixture evenly over top, pouring liquid over mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry-coke salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin by adding 1 cup hot liquid.
Add Coca-Cola. Put in refrigerator until gelatin begins to set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture in individual molds or square (8 x 8-inch) dish.

title: easy cheese souffle
directions: Shred bread, cube cheese and butter.
Mix with eggs and milk. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve immediately.

title: chili-ghetti
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and brown garlic, onion and beef.
Drain off excess fat, then add tomatoes and chili.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken tender; cool and cut fine with scissors or grind. Chop eggs, celery, onion, water chestnuts and pickles together. Add to chicken.
Mix well.
Add enough Miracle Whip salad dressing to make consistency desired.
Serve on crackers as appetizers or as sandwich spread or to stuff celery.

title: lasagna
directions: Put sauce on bottom of a 12 x 16-inch pan.
Place cooked lasagna in a layer.
Sprinkle a lot of Mozzarella cheese on noodles, then dot with Ricotta cheese.
Spread sauce again, then repeat.
End up with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: date-nut coffee cake
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter. Drizzle melted margarine evenly over topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
When cool, decorate with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: sour cream apple bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl; blend. Measure out 2
3/4 cups of this mixture and press into a

9 x 13 inch pan. Combine remaining crumb mixture with remaining ingredients. Mix well and spoon over crust. Bake at 350 for 25 to 35 minutes. Serve hot with ice cream or cold with whipped cream and a sprinkle of cinnamon.

title: mustard pineapple chops
directions: Season chicken or pork with salt and pepper.
Saute until golden.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Blend juice, mustard and honey.
Pour over meat.
Allow to simmer 30 minutes.
Top with pineapple.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch, if desired.

title: fig-strawberry preserves
directions: Mix figs and sugar together.
On medium heat, bring figs and sugar to a boil and add jello.
Boil 15 minutes longer.
Seal in jars according to directions.

title: perfect roast turkey with best-ever gravy
directions: Position rack in lowest position of oven and preheat to 325 degrees.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and butter first.
Add the other ingredients and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in greased casserole dish.
Heat chicken soup and sour cream until hot and pour over chicken.
Cover with the Ritz crumbs; drizzle melted oleo over the top.
Heat in a 350° oven until brown, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tangy marinated beef
directions: Two days before serving, place well trimmed meat in large bowl or pan.
In saucepan combine 3/4 cup water with rest of ingredients, except cornstarch.
Heat to boiling, then pour over the meat.
Cover and refrigerate two days.
Turn meat occasionally. About 3 hours before serving, remove from marinade and drain on paper towels.
Pat dry.
Strain and reserve marinade, discarding whole spices.
Brown meat on all sides in hot Teflon skillet over medium heat.
Add marinade, cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
To thicken gravy, mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons of water to form a paste.
Stir into gravy and continue cooking until slightly thickened.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 22 g, fat 15 g, calories 251.
One serving = 3 meat medium fat exchange, 1 vegetable exchange.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach; set aside.
Melt butter; add cream cheese and heat on warm, stirring, until blended.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Stir spinach into cream cheese mixture and mix well.
Line bottom of casserole dish with artichoke hearts.
Layer spinach mixture on top.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.

title: strawberry pizza (pie)
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Spread onto a cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before spreading topping and filling.

title: wendy's salsa
directions: Mix together. Bring to boil.
Cook at a simmer for 4 to 5 hours.
Pour into jars and process in water bath 20 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first five ingredients and spoon into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Spread crackers evenly over top and sprinkle with margarine.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute shrimp, onions and celery in butter.
Optional seasoning:
1/2 teaspoon thyme, pinch of celery seed, white pepper and salt.
Cut cream cheese into 1/4-inch pieces and lay in bottom of shell. Sprinkle Swiss cheese on top, then add sauteed shrimp, celery and onion.
Pour milk into egg mixture, mixing briefly and pour over all ingredients.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 350° and continue to bake for 1/2 hour longer.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch pan (head to trunk). Place chicken on top.
Mix together the soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Spread cheese over soup mixture.
Melt margarine; mix with bread crumbs. Spread bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Cook onions in reserved drippings until tender, not brown.
Add crumbled bacon to the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in 1/2-quart bean pot or casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: eight cup cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Press down with sugar dipped glass.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Keeps really well.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and cream well. Add milk and flour alternately (sift flour with baking powder). Add vanilla. Bake at 350° until done (when a toothpick comes out clean).

title: chicken salad in melon rings
directions: In a medium bowl, pour lemon juice over chicken.
Add celery, onion, salt, pepper, pimento, almonds, mayo and 1 cup grapes and toss.
Cover and chill.
Slice off ends of melons so seeds are exposed; scoop out seeds and membrane.
Cut each melon crosswise into 3 even slices.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix onion and garlic and saute.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer corn tortillas, half of ground beef, 1 can beans, 1 can black olives and 6 slices cheese.
Repeat layers again.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel in bowl.
Pour over casserole and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Add to mixture of soup, tomatoes and milk.
Crumble chips before opening bag.
Put 1/3 of chips in the dish, then 1 layer of chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat ending with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eggless-milkless-butterless cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, boil for 20 minutes.
Let stand until cold.
Slowly add 4 cups flour and 1 teaspoon soda.
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Use angel food cake pan which has been greased and floured.
This recipe makes a delicious fruit cake; just add chopped nuts and candied fruits, as many as desired.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in chunks.
Boil in salt water 20 minutes; drain.
Cook onions in 4 tablespoons butter or margarine. When tender, blend in flour and add a can of cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup milk, stirring constantly until it boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Add eggplant and pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with toasted bread crumbs or crackers.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 420° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sandy's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook in a 350° preheated oven until bubbly.

title: chicken potpie(chicken n' dumplin's)
directions: Mix eggs and milk together; add dry ingredients.
Stir until fairly smooth.
Add more flour to be able to handle dough.
Roll out on floured board to pie crust thickness.
Cut into squares (about 1-inch).
Drop squares into rapidly boiling broth one at a time.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until done, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shirley peltier's cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Add chicken broth and heat.
Break up cheese and stir in until melted.
Add milk.
Cook vegetables until barely tender in a little water.
Add to cream cheese mixture, water and all.
If it is too thick, add a little water or milk.
If it is too thin, mix cornstarch and water and add to soup.

title: sour cream and mushroom chicken
directions: Wrap each
chicken
breast
in a slice of bacon.
Place chicken breast
in	baking dish.
Combine soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.	Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mary's goulash
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
When it comes to a boil, add the rice. Cook until done or soft.
Drain and add to the hamburger after it is browned and drained in the skillet.
Then pour the soup over the top.
Heat to a boil and serve.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets in water until tender.
Dip in cold water and peel off skins.
Mix together sugar, water and vinegar.
Pour over beets and boil 10 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal at once.
Cook in water bath for 30 minutes.

title: bonnie's vegetable soup
directions: When adding canned vegetables, use juice too.
Cook until meat is tender on medium heat in large soup pot.

title: flitters
directions: Mix flour and water until not too thick or too thin.
Heat butter in skillet on stove until melted.
Pour batter in hot pan (enough for pancake).
Check for brownness; flip and brown that side.
Remove from pan and put in plate.
Put on butter and syrup. Eat until gone.
(If black, throw away and try again.)

title: party punch
directions: Combine all liquids except soda; mix well.
Add soda and ice cubes just before serving.
Float the fruit slices on top.
Yields 24 (4-ounce) servings.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Beat butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour (half at a time), blending well.
Beat egg whites in a pie plate until foamy.
Sprinkle walnuts on waxed paper.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls, roll in egg white, then in walnuts to coat all over.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down in center of each with thumb to make a hollow.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until firm and lightly golden.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Spoon preserves into each hollow.

title: aloha dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Serve with fresh fruit (pineapple, apples, strawberries, pears, etc.) and cubes of pound cake.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 400 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until top browns slightly.

title: dump in casserole
directions: Dump all ingredients into greased 2-quart casserole and mix. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with 1/3 of whole graham crackers. Set aside.
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over the graham crackers.
Layer 1/3 graham crackers on pudding mixture.
Pour remaining pudding and cover with remaining graham crackers.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chicken with red pepper-bulgaria(pille s cherven piper)
directions: Cut chicken into pieces, Saut for 5-6 minutes in butter.
Add onions and saut.
Add tomato sauce and flour stir well.
Add wine and simmer for 5-6 more minutes, add the rest of the ingredients and stir well.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes on low heat.
Serves 4-6.

title: my best devil food cake
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
(If you use powdered chocolate, mix with sugar.)
Add sugar, milk and beaten egg yolks. Blend well and cook, stirring until thick.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Divide all ingredients by 3 to make enough for 3 layers. Start with:
cake (crumbled up), Kahlua, pudding, Cool Whip or whipped cream, Heath bars.
Repeat 2 more times.

title: pasta salad
directions: In large bowl combine mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, basil and soup mix.
Add macaroni, toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours.
Yields 6 cups.

title: frankenmuth cranberry and orange relish
directions: Grind all fresh fruit until finely chopped.
Add sugar and mix.
Will taste better if made 2 or 3 days ahead of time.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all in casserole dish.
Put grated cheese over top and bake slowly, about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery until crisp and tender, about 8 minutes.

Mix with water chestnuts, pimento, almonds and cream of chicken soup. Place in baking dish and bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes. (Can be prepared ahead of time, just refrigerate until ready to bake, then put crumbs on top.) Recipe can be cut in half for smaller amount.

title: rigatoni and cheese casserole
directions: In large skillet, stirring frequently, lightly brown beef, onion and garlic over medium-high heat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and pepper.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.

title: jiffy hot bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Butter top of loaf when removed from oven.

title: cauliflower quiche
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions omitting salt; drain well and coarsely chop.
Place cauliflower on paper towels and squeeze until barely moist.
Coat a 9-inch pie plate with cooking spray.
Layer cauliflower, green pepper, onion and cheese in pie plate.
Combine remaining ingredients in container of electric blender; process 15 seconds or until well blended. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 servings (about 167 calories per serving).

title: cheese sausage dip
directions: Crumble sausage into small pieces, fry and drain grease.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well; form into balls and chill.
Mix chocolate chips and shortening. Mix while melting on stove or 3 minutes in microwave, stirring once.
Roll balls in chocolate mixture once it's melted, then refrigerate.

title: pizza burger
directions: Mix together.
Form into one large patty in 10-inch skillet and fry until done on one side and flip over after draining off grease for beef.
Cover top of patty with sliced mushrooms and pizza sauce.
When bottom side of patty is done, drain grease; cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Turn off heat and place lid on until cheese is melted.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: jello cranberry mold
directions: Use 1 cup hot water to dissolve jello.
Mix juice from pineapple with enough water to make 1 cup.
Mix well.
Chill until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cardinal krol's potatoes
directions: Slightly thaw potatoes.
Mix together other ingredients. Spread all on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix together all ingredients in a large casserole, except the potato chips.
Sprinkle the chips over the top.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Boil and stir 2 minutes longer.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into 4 dessert dishes.
Cover; chill.
Serve with a chocolate sauce.

title: sugar-free fluffy fruit dip
directions: In medium saucepan, combine dry pudding mix, dry gelatin and water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and starts to boil. Remove from heat. Place pan on a wire rack and allow to cool 5 minutes. Stir in cream cheese; mix well to combine. Refrigerate. Just before serving, let set at room temperature for 10 minutes.

title: war cake (no eggs)
directions: Mix brown sugar, hot water and shortening.
Add raisins.
Then add salt and spices.
Boil this for 5 minutes after it first bubbles.
Remove it from stone and let cool, being sure it is cooled completely.
Then add flour and 1 teaspoon soda that has been dissolved in hot water; mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: mother's prize spice cake
directions: Grease	and
line
two 9-inch cake pans with wax paper. Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, cream well.
Sift together flour and
spices.
Add alternately the flour mixture and the buttermilk.
Mix
well.
Bake
at
for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove
from oven; let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan; peel off paper.
Frost with caramel frosting.

title: florida punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in medium sized saucepan; boil for 3 minutes until syrupy.
Chill.
Combine 1 liter of ginger ale with orange slices and cherries in a mold; freeze.
Combine chilled sugar-water and juices in large punch bowl.
Before serving, add 2 liters of chilled ginger ale and ice mold.
Makes about 40 (1/2 cup) servings.
